221std::unique_ptr<CodeGen_LLVM> CodeGen_LLVM::new_for_target(const Target &target, llvm::LLVMContext &context) {
222 std::unique_ptr<CodeGen_LLVM> result;
223 if (target.arch == Target::X86) {
224 result = new_CodeGen_X86(target);
225 } else if (target.arch == Target::ARM) {
226 result = new_CodeGen_ARM(target);
227 } else if (target.arch == Target::MIPS) {
228 result = new_CodeGen_MIPS(target);
229 } else if (target.arch == Target::POWERPC) {
230 result = new_CodeGen_PowerPC(target);
231 } else if (target.arch == Target::Hexagon) {
232 result = new_CodeGen_Hexagon(target);
233 } else if (target.arch == Target::WebAssembly) {
234 result = new_CodeGen_WebAssembly(target);
235 } else if (target.arch == Target::RISCV) {
236 result = new_CodeGen_RISCV(target);
237 }
238 user_assert(result) << "Unknown target architecture: " << target.to_string() << "\n";
239 result->set_context(context);
240 return result;
241}

243void CodeGen_LLVM::initialize_llvm() {
244 static std::once_flag init_llvm_once;
245 std::call_once(init_llvm_once, []() {
246 // You can hack in command-line args to llvm with the
247 // environment variable HL_LLVM_ARGS, e.g. HL_LLVM_ARGS="-print-after-all"
248 std::string args = get_env_variable("HL_LLVM_ARGS");
249 if (!args.empty()) {
250 vector<std::string> arg_vec = split_string(args, " ");
251 vector<const char *> c_arg_vec;
252 c_arg_vec.push_back("llc");
253 for (const std::string &s : arg_vec) {
254 c_arg_vec.push_back(s.c_str());
255 }
256 cl::ParseCommandLineOptions((int)(c_arg_vec.size()), &c_arg_vec[0], "Halide compiler\n");
257 }
258
259 InitializeNativeTarget();
260 InitializeNativeTargetAsmPrinter();
261 InitializeNativeTargetAsmParser();
262
263#define LLVM_TARGET(target) \
264 Initialize##target##Target();
265#include <llvm/Config/Targets.def>
266#undef LLVM_TARGET
267
268#define LLVM_ASM_PARSER(target) \
269 Initialize##target##AsmParser();
270#include <llvm/Config/AsmParsers.def>
271#undef LLVM_ASM_PARSER
272
273#define LLVM_ASM_PRINTER(target) \
274 Initialize##target##AsmPrinter();
275#include <llvm/Config/AsmPrinters.def>
276#include <utility>
277#undef LLVM_ASM_PRINTER
278 });
279}

281void CodeGen_LLVM::init_context() {
282 // Ensure our IRBuilder is using the current context.
283 delete builder;
284 builder = new IRBuilder<>(*context);
285
286 // Branch weights for very likely branches
287 llvm::MDBuilder md_builder(*context);
288 very_likely_branch = md_builder.createBranchWeights(1 << 30, 0);
289 default_fp_math_md = md_builder.createFPMath(0.0);
290 strict_fp_math_md = md_builder.createFPMath(0.0);
291 builder->setDefaultFPMathTag(default_fp_math_md);
292 llvm::FastMathFlags fast_flags;
293 fast_flags.setNoNaNs();
294 fast_flags.setNoInfs();
295 fast_flags.setNoSignedZeros();
296 // Don't use approximate reciprocals for division. It's too inaccurate even for Halide.
297 // fast_flags.setAllowReciprocal();
298 // Theoretically, setAllowReassoc could be setUnsafeAlgebra for earlier versions, but that
299 // turns on all the flags.
300 fast_flags.setAllowReassoc();
301 fast_flags.setAllowContract(true);
302 fast_flags.setApproxFunc();
303 builder->setFastMathFlags(fast_flags);
304
305 // Define some types
306 void_t = llvm::Type::getVoidTy(*context);
307 i1_t = llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(*context);
308 i8_t = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*context);
309 i16_t = llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(*context);
310 i32_t = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(*context);
311 i64_t = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(*context);
312 f16_t = llvm::Type::getHalfTy(*context);
313 f32_t = llvm::Type::getFloatTy(*context);
314 f64_t = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(*context);
315}

317void CodeGen_LLVM::init_module() {

319
320 // Start with a module containing the initial module for this target.
321 module = get_initial_module_for_target(target, context);

324void CodeGen_LLVM::add_external_code(const Module &halide_module) {
325 for (const ExternalCode &code_blob : halide_module.external_code()) {
326 if (code_blob.is_for_cpu_target(get_target())) {
327 add_bitcode_to_module(context, *module, code_blob.contents(), code_blob.name());
328 }
329 }

338struct MangledNames {
339 string simple_name;
340 string extern_name;
341 string argv_name;
342 string metadata_name;
343};
344
345MangledNames get_mangled_names(const std::string &name,
346 LinkageType linkage,
347 NameMangling mangling,
348 const std::vector<LoweredArgument> &args,
349 const Target &target) {
350 std::vector<std::string> namespaces;
351 MangledNames names;
352 names.simple_name = extract_namespaces(name, namespaces);
353 names.extern_name = names.simple_name;
354 names.argv_name = names.simple_name + "_argv";
355 names.metadata_name = names.simple_name + "_metadata";
356
357 if (linkage != LinkageType::Internal &&
358 ((mangling == NameMangling::Default &&
359 target.has_feature(Target::CPlusPlusMangling)) ||
360 mangling == NameMangling::CPlusPlus)) {
361 std::vector<ExternFuncArgument> mangle_args;
362 for (const auto &arg : args) {
363 if (arg.kind == Argument::InputScalar) {
364 mangle_args.emplace_back(make_zero(arg.type));
365 } else if (arg.kind == Argument::InputBuffer ||
366 arg.kind == Argument::OutputBuffer) {
367 mangle_args.emplace_back(Buffer<>());
368 }
369 }
370 names.extern_name = cplusplus_function_mangled_name(names.simple_name, namespaces, type_of<int>(), mangle_args, target);
371 halide_handle_cplusplus_type inner_type(halide_cplusplus_type_name(halide_cplusplus_type_name::Simple, "void"), {}, {},
372 {halide_handle_cplusplus_type::Pointer, halide_handle_cplusplus_type::Pointer});
373 Type void_star_star(Handle(1, &inner_type));
374 names.argv_name = cplusplus_function_mangled_name(names.argv_name, namespaces, type_of<int>(), {ExternFuncArgument(make_zero(void_star_star))}, target);
375 names.metadata_name = cplusplus_function_mangled_name(names.metadata_name, namespaces, type_of<const struct halide_filter_metadata_t *>(), {}, target);
376 }
377 return names;
378}
379
380MangledNames get_mangled_names(const LoweredFunc &f, const Target &target) {
381 return get_mangled_names(f.name, f.linkage, f.name_mangling, f.args, target);
382}

386llvm::FunctionType *CodeGen_LLVM::signature_to_type(const ExternSignature &signature) {
387 internal_assert(void_t != nullptr && halide_buffer_t_type != nullptr);
388 llvm::Type *ret_type =
389 signature.is_void_return() ? void_t : llvm_type_of(upgrade_type_for_argument_passing(signature.ret_type()));
390 std::vector<llvm::Type *> llvm_arg_types;
391 for (const Type &t : signature.arg_types()) {
392 if (t == type_of<struct halide_buffer_t *>()) {
393 llvm_arg_types.push_back(halide_buffer_t_type->getPointerTo());
394 } else {
395 llvm_arg_types.push_back(llvm_type_of(upgrade_type_for_argument_passing(t)));
396 }
397 }
398
399 return llvm::FunctionType::get(ret_type, llvm_arg_types, false);
400}

402/*static*/
403std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> CodeGen_LLVM::compile_trampolines(
404 const Target &target,
405 llvm::LLVMContext &context,
406 const std::string &suffix,
407 const std::vector<std::pair<std::string, ExternSignature>> &externs) {
408 std::unique_ptr<CodeGen_LLVM> codegen(new_for_target(target, context));
409 codegen->init_codegen("trampolines" + suffix);
410 for (const std::pair<std::string, ExternSignature> &e : externs) {
411 const std::string &callee_name = e.first;
412 const std::string wrapper_name = callee_name + suffix;
413 llvm::FunctionType *fn_type = codegen->signature_to_type(e.second);
414 // callee might already be present for builtins, e.g. halide_print
415 llvm::Function *callee = codegen->module->getFunction(callee_name);
416 if (!callee) {
417 callee = llvm::Function::Create(fn_type, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, callee_name, codegen->module.get());
418 }
419 codegen->add_argv_wrapper(callee, wrapper_name, /*result_in_argv*/ true);
420 }
421 return codegen->finish_codegen();
422}

424void CodeGen_LLVM::init_codegen(const std::string &name, bool any_strict_float) {
425 init_module();
426
427 internal_assert(module && context);
428
429 debug(1) << "Target triple of initial module: " << module->getTargetTriple() << "\n";
430
431 module->setModuleIdentifier(name);
432
433 // Add some target specific info to the module as metadata.
434 module->addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "halide_use_soft_float_abi", use_soft_float_abi() ? 1 : 0);
435 module->addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "halide_mcpu", MDString::get(*context, mcpu()));
436 module->addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "halide_mattrs", MDString::get(*context, mattrs()));
437 module->addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "halide_mabi", MDString::get(*context, mabi()));
438 module->addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "halide_use_pic", use_pic() ? 1 : 0);
439 module->addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "halide_use_large_code_model", llvm_large_code_model ? 1 : 0);
440 module->addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "halide_per_instruction_fast_math_flags", any_strict_float);
441
442 // Ensure some types we need are defined
443 halide_buffer_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_buffer_t");
444 internal_assert(halide_buffer_t_type) << "Did not find halide_buffer_t in initial module";
445
446 type_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_type_t");
447 internal_assert(type_t_type) << "Did not find halide_type_t in initial module";
448
449 dimension_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_dimension_t");
450 internal_assert(dimension_t_type) << "Did not find halide_dimension_t in initial module";
451
452 metadata_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_filter_metadata_t");
453 internal_assert(metadata_t_type) << "Did not find halide_filter_metadata_t in initial module";
454
455 argument_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_filter_argument_t");
456 internal_assert(argument_t_type) << "Did not find halide_filter_argument_t in initial module";
457
458 scalar_value_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_scalar_value_t");
459 internal_assert(scalar_value_t_type) << "Did not find halide_scalar_value_t in initial module";
460
461 device_interface_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_device_interface_t");
462 internal_assert(device_interface_t_type) << "Did not find halide_device_interface_t in initial module";
463
464 pseudostack_slot_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_pseudostack_slot_t");
465 internal_assert(pseudostack_slot_t_type) << "Did not find halide_pseudostack_slot_t in initial module";
466
467 semaphore_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_semaphore_t");
468 internal_assert(semaphore_t_type) << "Did not find halide_semaphore_t in initial module";
469
470 semaphore_acquire_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_semaphore_acquire_t");
471 internal_assert(semaphore_acquire_t_type) << "Did not find halide_semaphore_acquire_t in initial module";
472
473 parallel_task_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_parallel_task_t");
474 internal_assert(parallel_task_t_type) << "Did not find halide_parallel_task_t in initial module";
475}
476
477std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> CodeGen_LLVM::compile(const Module &input) {
478 init_codegen(input.name(), input.any_strict_float());
479
480 internal_assert(module && context && builder)
481 << "The CodeGen_LLVM subclass should have made an initial module before calling CodeGen_LLVM::compile\n";
482
483 add_external_code(input);
484
485 // Generate the code for this module.
486 debug(1) << "Generating llvm bitcode...\n";
487 for (const auto &b : input.buffers()) {
488 compile_buffer(b);
489 }
490 for (const auto &f : input.functions()) {
491 const auto names = get_mangled_names(f, get_target());
492
493 run_with_large_stack([&]() {
494 compile_func(f, names.simple_name, names.extern_name);
495 });
496
497 // If the Func is externally visible, also create the argv wrapper and metadata.
498 // (useful for calling from JIT and other machine interfaces).
499 if (f.linkage == LinkageType::ExternalPlusMetadata) {
500 llvm::Function *wrapper = add_argv_wrapper(function, names.argv_name);
501 llvm::Function *metadata_getter = embed_metadata_getter(names.metadata_name,
502 names.simple_name, f.args, input.get_metadata_name_map());
503
504 if (target.has_feature(Target::Matlab)) {
505 define_matlab_wrapper(module.get(), wrapper, metadata_getter);
506 }
507 }
508 }
509
510 debug(2) << module.get() << "\n";
511
512 return finish_codegen();
513}
514
515std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> CodeGen_LLVM::finish_codegen() {
516 // Verify the module is ok
517 internal_assert(!verifyModule(*module, &llvm::errs()));
518 debug(2) << "Done generating llvm bitcode\n";
519
520 // Optimize
521 CodeGen_LLVM::optimize_module();
522
523 if (target.has_feature(Target::EmbedBitcode)) {
524 std::string halide_command = "halide target=" + target.to_string();
525 embed_bitcode(module.get(), halide_command);
526 }
527
528 // Disown the module and return it.
529 return std::move(module);
530}
531
532void CodeGen_LLVM::begin_func(LinkageType linkage, const std::string &name,
533 const std::string &extern_name, const std::vector<LoweredArgument> &args) {
534 current_function_args = args;
535
536 // Deduce the types of the arguments to our function
537 vector<llvm::Type *> arg_types(args.size());
538 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.size(); i++) {
539 if (args[i].is_buffer()) {
540 arg_types[i] = halide_buffer_t_type->getPointerTo();
541 } else {
542 arg_types[i] = llvm_type_of(upgrade_type_for_argument_passing(args[i].type));
543 }
544 }
545 FunctionType *func_t = FunctionType::get(i32_t, arg_types, false);
546
547 // Make our function. There may already be a declaration of it.
548 function = module->getFunction(extern_name);
549 if (!function) {
550 function = llvm::Function::Create(func_t, llvm_linkage(linkage), extern_name, module.get());
551 } else {
552 user_assert(function->isDeclaration())
553 << "Another function with the name " << extern_name
554 << " already exists in the same module\n";
555 if (func_t != function->getFunctionType()) {
556 std::cerr << "Desired function type for " << extern_name << ":\n";
557 func_t->print(dbgs(), true);
558 std::cerr << "Declared function type of " << extern_name << ":\n";
559 function->getFunctionType()->print(dbgs(), true);
560 user_error << "Cannot create a function with a declaration of mismatched type.\n";
561 }
562 }
563 set_function_attributes_for_target(function, target);
564
565 // Mark the buffer args as no alias
566 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.size(); i++) {
567 if (args[i].is_buffer()) {
568 function->addParamAttr(i, Attribute::NoAlias);
569 }
570 }
571
572 debug(1) << "Generating llvm bitcode prolog for function " << name << "...\n";
573
574 // Null out the destructor block.
575 destructor_block = nullptr;
576
577 // Make the initial basic block
578 BasicBlock *block = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "entry", function);
579 builder->SetInsertPoint(block);
580
581 // Put the arguments in the symbol table
582 {
583 size_t i = 0;
584 for (auto &arg : function->args()) {
585 if (args[i].is_buffer()) {
586 // Track this buffer name so that loads and stores from it
587 // don't try to be too aligned.
588 external_buffer.insert(args[i].name);
589 sym_push(args[i].name + ".buffer", &arg);
590 } else {
591 Type passed_type = upgrade_type_for_argument_passing(args[i].type);
592 if (args[i].type != passed_type) {
593 llvm::Value *a = builder->CreateBitCast(&arg, llvm_type_of(args[i].type));
594 sym_push(args[i].name, a);
595 } else {
596 sym_push(args[i].name, &arg);
597 }
598 }
599
600 i++;
601 }
602 }
603}
604
605void CodeGen_LLVM::end_func(const std::vector<LoweredArgument> &args) {
606 return_with_error_code(ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0));
607
608 // Remove the arguments from the symbol table
609 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.size(); i++) {
610 if (args[i].is_buffer()) {
611 sym_pop(args[i].name + ".buffer");
612 } else {
613 sym_pop(args[i].name);
614 }
615 }
616
617 internal_assert(!verifyFunction(*function, &llvm::errs()));
618
619 current_function_args.clear();
620}
621
622void CodeGen_LLVM::compile_func(const LoweredFunc &f, const std::string &simple_name,
623 const std::string &extern_name) {
624 // Generate the function declaration and argument unpacking code.
625 begin_func(f.linkage, simple_name, extern_name, f.args);
626
627 // If building with MSAN, ensure that calls to halide_msan_annotate_buffer_is_initialized()
628 // happen for every output buffer if the function succeeds.
629 if (f.linkage != LinkageType::Internal &&
630 target.has_feature(Target::MSAN)) {
631 llvm::Function *annotate_buffer_fn =
632 module->getFunction("halide_msan_annotate_buffer_is_initialized_as_destructor");
633 internal_assert(annotate_buffer_fn)
634 << "Could not find halide_msan_annotate_buffer_is_initialized_as_destructor in module\n";
635 annotate_buffer_fn->addParamAttr(0, Attribute::NoAlias);
636 for (const auto &arg : f.args) {
637 if (arg.kind == Argument::OutputBuffer) {
638 register_destructor(annotate_buffer_fn, sym_get(arg.name + ".buffer"), OnSuccess);
639 }
640 }
641 }
642
643 // Generate the function body.
644 debug(1) << "Generating llvm bitcode for function " << f.name << "...\n";
645 f.body.accept(this);
646
647 // Clean up and return.
648 end_func(f.args);
649}

651// Given a range of iterators of constant ints, get a corresponding vector of llvm::Constant.
652template<typename It>
653std::vector<llvm::Constant *> get_constants(llvm::Type *t, It begin, It end) {
654 std::vector<llvm::Constant *> ret;
655 for (It i = begin; i != end; i++) {
656 ret.push_back(ConstantInt::get(t, *i));
657 }
658 return ret;
659}
660
661BasicBlock *CodeGen_LLVM::get_destructor_block() {
662 if (!destructor_block) {
663 // Create it if it doesn't exist.
664 IRBuilderBase::InsertPoint here = builder->saveIP();
665 destructor_block = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "destructor_block", function);
666 builder->SetInsertPoint(destructor_block);
667 // The first instruction in the destructor block is a phi node
668 // that collects the error code.
669 PHINode *error_code = builder->CreatePHI(i32_t, 0);
670
671 // Calls to destructors will get inserted here.
672
673 // The last instruction is the return op that returns it.
674 builder->CreateRet(error_code);
675
676 // Jump back to where we were.
677 builder->restoreIP(here);
678 }
679 internal_assert(destructor_block->getParent() == function);
680 return destructor_block;
681}
682
683Value *CodeGen_LLVM::register_destructor(llvm::Function *destructor_fn, Value *obj, DestructorType when) {
684
685 // Create a null-initialized stack slot to track this object
686 llvm::Type *void_ptr = i8_t->getPointerTo();
687 llvm::Value *stack_slot = create_alloca_at_entry(void_ptr, 1, true);
688
689 // Cast the object to llvm's representation of void *
690 obj = builder->CreatePointerCast(obj, void_ptr);
691
692 // Put it in the stack slot
693 builder->CreateStore(obj, stack_slot);
694
695 // Passing the constant null as the object means the destructor
696 // will never get called.
697 {
698 llvm::Constant *c = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(obj);
699 if (c && c->isNullValue()) {
700 internal_error << "Destructors must take a non-null object\n";
701 }
702 }
703
704 // Switch to the destructor block, and add code that cleans up
705 // this object if the contents of the stack slot is not nullptr.
706 IRBuilderBase::InsertPoint here = builder->saveIP();
707 BasicBlock *dtors = get_destructor_block();
708
709 builder->SetInsertPoint(dtors->getFirstNonPHI());
710
711 PHINode *error_code = dyn_cast<PHINode>(dtors->begin());
712 internal_assert(error_code) << "The destructor block is supposed to start with a phi node\n";
713
714 llvm::Value *should_call = nullptr;
715 switch (when) {
716 case Always:
717 should_call = ConstantInt::get(i1_t, 1);
718 break;
719 case OnError:
720 should_call = builder->CreateIsNotNull(error_code);
721 break;
722 case OnSuccess:
723 should_call = builder->CreateIsNull(error_code);
724 break;
725 }
726 llvm::Function *call_destructor = module->getFunction("call_destructor");
727 internal_assert(call_destructor);
728 internal_assert(destructor_fn);
729 internal_assert(should_call);
730 Value *args[] = {get_user_context(), destructor_fn, stack_slot, should_call};
731 builder->CreateCall(call_destructor, args);
732
733 // Switch back to the original location
734 builder->restoreIP(here);
735
736 // Return the stack slot so that it's possible to cleanup the object early.
737 return stack_slot;
738}
739
740void CodeGen_LLVM::trigger_destructor(llvm::Function *destructor_fn, Value *stack_slot) {
741 llvm::Function *call_destructor = module->getFunction("call_destructor");
742 internal_assert(call_destructor);
743 internal_assert(destructor_fn);
744 stack_slot = builder->CreatePointerCast(stack_slot, i8_t->getPointerTo()->getPointerTo());
745 Value *should_call = ConstantInt::get(i1_t, 1);
746 Value *args[] = {get_user_context(), destructor_fn, stack_slot, should_call};
747 builder->CreateCall(call_destructor, args);
748}
749
750void CodeGen_LLVM::compile_buffer(const Buffer<> &buf) {
751 // Embed the buffer declaration as a global.
752 internal_assert(buf.defined());
753
754 user_assert(buf.data())
755 << "Can't embed buffer " << buf.name() << " because it has a null host pointer.\n";
756 user_assert(!buf.device_dirty())
757 << "Can't embed Image \"" << buf.name() << "\""
758 << " because it has a dirty device pointer\n";
759
760 Constant *type_fields[] = {
761 ConstantInt::get(i8_t, buf.type().code()),
762 ConstantInt::get(i8_t, buf.type().bits()),
763 ConstantInt::get(i16_t, buf.type().lanes())};
764
765 Constant *shape = nullptr;
766 if (buf.dimensions()) {
767 size_t shape_size = buf.dimensions() * sizeof(halide_dimension_t);
768 vector<char> shape_blob((char *)buf.raw_buffer()->dim, (char *)buf.raw_buffer()->dim + shape_size);
769 shape = create_binary_blob(shape_blob, buf.name() + ".shape");
770 shape = ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(shape, dimension_t_type->getPointerTo());
771 } else {
772 shape = ConstantPointerNull::get(dimension_t_type->getPointerTo());
773 }
774
775 // For now, we assume buffers that aren't scalar are constant,
776 // while scalars can be mutated. This accommodates all our existing
777 // use cases, which is that all buffers are constant, except those
778 // used to store stateful module information in offloading runtimes.
779 bool constant = buf.dimensions() != 0;
780
781 vector<char> data_blob((const char *)buf.data(), (const char *)buf.data() + buf.size_in_bytes());
782
783 Constant *fields[] = {
784 ConstantInt::get(i64_t, 0), // device
785 ConstantPointerNull::get(device_interface_t_type->getPointerTo()), // device_interface
786 create_binary_blob(data_blob, buf.name() + ".data", constant), // host
787 ConstantInt::get(i64_t, halide_buffer_flag_host_dirty), // flags
788 ConstantStruct::get(type_t_type, type_fields), // type
789 ConstantInt::get(i32_t, buf.dimensions()), // dimensions
790 shape, // dim
791 ConstantPointerNull::get(i8_t->getPointerTo()), // padding
792 };
793 Constant *buffer_struct = ConstantStruct::get(halide_buffer_t_type, fields);
794
795 // Embed the halide_buffer_t and make it point to the data array.
796 GlobalVariable *global = new GlobalVariable(*module, halide_buffer_t_type,
797 false, GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
798 nullptr, buf.name() + ".buffer");
799 global->setInitializer(buffer_struct);
800
801 // Finally, dump it in the symbol table
802 Constant *zero[] = {ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0)};
803 Constant *global_ptr = ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(halide_buffer_t_type, global, zero);
804 sym_push(buf.name() + ".buffer", global_ptr);
805}
806
807Constant *CodeGen_LLVM::embed_constant_scalar_value_t(const Expr &e) {
808 if (!e.defined()) {
809 return Constant::getNullValue(scalar_value_t_type->getPointerTo());
810 }
811
812 internal_assert(!e.type().is_handle()) << "Should never see Handle types here.";
813
814 llvm::Value *val = codegen(e);
815 llvm::Constant *constant = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(val);
816 internal_assert(constant);
817
818 // Verify that the size of the LLVM value is the size we expected.
819 internal_assert((uint64_t)constant->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == (uint64_t)e.type().bits());
820
821 // It's important that we allocate a full scalar_value_t_type here,
822 // even if the type of the value is smaller; downstream consumers should
823 // be able to correctly load an entire scalar_value_t_type regardless of its
824 // type, and if we emit just (say) a uint8 value here, the pointer may be
825 // misaligned and/or the storage after may be unmapped. LLVM doesn't support
826 // unions directly, so we'll fake it by making a constant array of the elements
827 // we need, setting the first to the constant we want, and setting the rest
828 // to all-zeros. (This happens to work because sizeof(halide_scalar_value_t) is evenly
829 // divisible by sizeof(any-union-field.)
830
831 const size_t value_size = e.type().bytes();
832 internal_assert(value_size > 0 && value_size <= sizeof(halide_scalar_value_t));
833
834 const size_t array_size = sizeof(halide_scalar_value_t) / value_size;
835 internal_assert(array_size * value_size == sizeof(halide_scalar_value_t));
836
837 vector<Constant *> array_entries(array_size, Constant::getNullValue(constant->getType()));
838 array_entries[0] = constant;
839
840 llvm::ArrayType *array_type = ArrayType::get(constant->getType(), array_size);
841 GlobalVariable *storage = new GlobalVariable(
842 *module,
843 array_type,
844 /*isConstant*/ true,
845 GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
846 ConstantArray::get(array_type, array_entries));
847
848 // Ensure that the storage is aligned for halide_scalar_value_t
849 storage->setAlignment(llvm::Align((int)sizeof(halide_scalar_value_t)));
850
851 Constant *zero[] = {ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0)};
852 return ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
853 ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(array_type, storage, zero),
854 scalar_value_t_type->getPointerTo());
855}
856
857Constant *CodeGen_LLVM::embed_constant_expr(Expr e, llvm::Type *t) {
858 internal_assert(t != scalar_value_t_type);
859
860 if (!e.defined()) {
861 return Constant::getNullValue(t->getPointerTo());
862 }
863
864 internal_assert(!e.type().is_handle()) << "Should never see Handle types here.";
865 if (!is_const(e)) {
866 e = simplify(e);
867 internal_assert(is_const(e)) << "Should only see constant values for estimates.";
868 }
869
870 llvm::Value *val = codegen(e);
871 llvm::Constant *constant = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(val);
872 internal_assert(constant);
873
874 GlobalVariable *storage = new GlobalVariable(
875 *module,
876 constant->getType(),
877 /*isConstant*/ true,
878 GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
879 constant);
880
881 Constant *zero[] = {ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0)};
882 return ConstantExpr::getBitCast(
883 ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(constant->getType(), storage, zero),
884 t->getPointerTo());
885}
886
887// Make a wrapper to call the function with an array of pointer
888// args. This is easier for the JIT to call than a function with an
889// unknown (at compile time) argument list. If result_in_argv is false,
890// the internal function result is returned as the wrapper function
891// result; if result_in_argv is true, the internal function result
892// is stored as the last item in the argv list (which must be one
893// longer than the number of arguments), and the wrapper's actual
894// return type is always 'void'.
895llvm::Function *CodeGen_LLVM::add_argv_wrapper(llvm::Function *fn,
896 const std::string &name,
897 bool result_in_argv) {
898 llvm::Type *wrapper_result_type = result_in_argv ? void_t : i32_t;
899 llvm::Type *wrapper_args_t[] = {i8_t->getPointerTo()->getPointerTo()};
900 llvm::FunctionType *wrapper_func_t = llvm::FunctionType::get(wrapper_result_type, wrapper_args_t, false);
901 llvm::Function *wrapper_func = llvm::Function::Create(wrapper_func_t, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, name, module.get());
902 llvm::BasicBlock *wrapper_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(module->getContext(), "entry", wrapper_func);
903 builder->SetInsertPoint(wrapper_block);
904
905 llvm::Value *arg_array = iterator_to_pointer(wrapper_func->arg_begin());
906 std::vector<llvm::Value *> wrapper_args;
907 for (llvm::Function::arg_iterator i = fn->arg_begin(); i != fn->arg_end(); i++) {
908 // Get the address of the nth argument
909 llvm::Value *ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP1_32(arg_array, wrapper_args.size());
910 ptr = builder->CreateLoad(ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), ptr);
911 if (i->getType() == halide_buffer_t_type->getPointerTo()) {
912 // Cast the argument to a halide_buffer_t *
913 wrapper_args.push_back(builder->CreatePointerCast(ptr, halide_buffer_t_type->getPointerTo()));
914 } else {
915 // Cast to the appropriate type and load
916 ptr = builder->CreatePointerCast(ptr, i->getType()->getPointerTo());
917 wrapper_args.push_back(builder->CreateLoad(ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), ptr));
918 }
919 }
920 debug(4) << "Creating call from wrapper to actual function\n";
921 llvm::CallInst *result = builder->CreateCall(fn, wrapper_args);
922 // This call should never inline
923 result->setIsNoInline();
924
925 if (result_in_argv) {
926 llvm::Value *result_in_argv_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP1_32(arg_array, wrapper_args.size());
927 if (fn->getReturnType() != void_t) {
928 result_in_argv_ptr = builder->CreateLoad(result_in_argv_ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), result_in_argv_ptr);
929 // Cast to the appropriate type and store
930 result_in_argv_ptr = builder->CreatePointerCast(result_in_argv_ptr, fn->getReturnType()->getPointerTo());
931 builder->CreateStore(result, result_in_argv_ptr);
932 }
933 builder->CreateRetVoid();
934 } else {
935 // We could probably support other types as return values,
936 // but int32 results are all that have actually been tested.
937 internal_assert(fn->getReturnType() == i32_t);
938 builder->CreateRet(result);
939 }
940 internal_assert(!verifyFunction(*wrapper_func, &llvm::errs()));
941 return wrapper_func;
942}
943
944llvm::Function *CodeGen_LLVM::embed_metadata_getter(const std::string &metadata_name,
945 const std::string &function_name, const std::vector<LoweredArgument> &args,
946 const std::map<std::string, std::string> &metadata_name_map) {
947 Constant *zero = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0);
948
949 const int num_args = (int)args.size();
950
951 auto map_string = [&metadata_name_map](const std::string &from) -> std::string {
952 auto it = metadata_name_map.find(from);
953 return it == metadata_name_map.end() ? from : it->second;
954 };
955
956 vector<Constant *> arguments_array_entries;
957 for (int arg = 0; arg < num_args; ++arg) {
958
959 StructType *type_t_type = get_llvm_struct_type_by_name(module.get(), "struct.halide_type_t");
960 internal_assert(type_t_type) << "Did not find halide_type_t in module.\n";
961
962 Constant *type_fields[] = {
963 ConstantInt::get(i8_t, args[arg].type.code()),
964 ConstantInt::get(i8_t, args[arg].type.bits()),
965 ConstantInt::get(i16_t, 1)};
966 Constant *type = ConstantStruct::get(type_t_type, type_fields);
967
968 auto argument_estimates = args[arg].argument_estimates;
969 if (args[arg].type.is_handle()) {
970 // Handle values are always emitted into metadata as "undefined", regardless of
971 // what sort of Expr is provided.
972 argument_estimates = ArgumentEstimates{};
973 }
974
975 Constant *buffer_estimates_array_ptr;
976 if (args[arg].is_buffer() && !argument_estimates.buffer_estimates.empty()) {
977 internal_assert((int)argument_estimates.buffer_estimates.size() == args[arg].dimensions);
978 vector<Constant *> buffer_estimates_array_entries;
979 for (const auto &be : argument_estimates.buffer_estimates) {
980 Expr min = be.min;
981 if (min.defined()) {
982 min = cast<int64_t>(min);
983 }
984 Expr extent = be.extent;
985 if (extent.defined()) {
986 extent = cast<int64_t>(extent);
987 }
988 buffer_estimates_array_entries.push_back(embed_constant_expr(min, i64_t));
989 buffer_estimates_array_entries.push_back(embed_constant_expr(extent, i64_t));
990 }
991
992 llvm::ArrayType *buffer_estimates_array = ArrayType::get(i64_t->getPointerTo(), buffer_estimates_array_entries.size());
993 GlobalVariable *buffer_estimates_array_storage = new GlobalVariable(
994 *module,
995 buffer_estimates_array,
996 /*isConstant*/ true,
997 GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
998 ConstantArray::get(buffer_estimates_array, buffer_estimates_array_entries));
999
1000 Value *zeros[] = {zero, zero};
1001 buffer_estimates_array_ptr = ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(buffer_estimates_array, buffer_estimates_array_storage, zeros);
1002 } else {
1003 buffer_estimates_array_ptr = Constant::getNullValue(i64_t->getPointerTo()->getPointerTo());
1004 }
1005
1006 Constant *argument_fields[] = {
1007 create_string_constant(map_string(args[arg].name)),
1008 ConstantInt::get(i32_t, args[arg].kind),
1009 ConstantInt::get(i32_t, args[arg].dimensions),
1010 type,
1011 embed_constant_scalar_value_t(argument_estimates.scalar_def),
1012 embed_constant_scalar_value_t(argument_estimates.scalar_min),
1013 embed_constant_scalar_value_t(argument_estimates.scalar_max),
1014 embed_constant_scalar_value_t(argument_estimates.scalar_estimate),
1015 buffer_estimates_array_ptr};
1016 arguments_array_entries.push_back(ConstantStruct::get(argument_t_type, argument_fields));
1017 }
1018 llvm::ArrayType *arguments_array = ArrayType::get(argument_t_type, num_args);
1019 GlobalVariable *arguments_array_storage = new GlobalVariable(
1020 *module,
1021 arguments_array,
1022 /*isConstant*/ true,
1023 GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
1024 ConstantArray::get(arguments_array, arguments_array_entries));
1025
1026 Constant *version = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, halide_filter_metadata_t::VERSION);
1027
1028 Value *zeros[] = {zero, zero};
1029 Constant *metadata_fields[] = {
1030 /* version */ version,
1031 /* num_arguments */ ConstantInt::get(i32_t, num_args),
1032 /* arguments */ ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(arguments_array, arguments_array_storage, zeros),
1033 /* target */ create_string_constant(map_string(target.to_string())),
1034 /* name */ create_string_constant(map_string(function_name))};
1035
1036 GlobalVariable *metadata_storage = new GlobalVariable(
1037 *module,
1038 metadata_t_type,
1039 /*isConstant*/ true,
1040 GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
1041 ConstantStruct::get(metadata_t_type, metadata_fields),
1042 metadata_name + "_storage");
1043
1044 llvm::FunctionType *func_t = llvm::FunctionType::get(metadata_t_type->getPointerTo(), false);
1045 llvm::Function *metadata_getter = llvm::Function::Create(func_t, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, metadata_name, module.get());
1046 llvm::BasicBlock *block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(module->getContext(), "entry", metadata_getter);
1047 builder->SetInsertPoint(block);
1048 builder->CreateRet(metadata_storage);
1049 internal_assert(!verifyFunction(*metadata_getter, &llvm::errs()));
1050
1051 return metadata_getter;
1052}

1057
1058void CodeGen_LLVM::optimize_module() {
1059 debug(3) << "Optimizing module\n";
1060
1061 auto time_start = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
1062
1063 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
1064 module->print(dbgs(), nullptr, false, true);
1065 }
1066
1067 std::unique_ptr<TargetMachine> tm = make_target_machine(*module);
1068
1069 // At present, we default to *enabling* LLVM loop optimization,
1070 // unless DisableLLVMLoopOpt is set; we're going to flip this to defaulting
1071 // to *not* enabling these optimizations (and removing the DisableLLVMLoopOpt feature).
1072 // See https://github.com/halide/Halide/issues/4113 for more info.
1073 // (Note that setting EnableLLVMLoopOpt always enables loop opt, regardless
1074 // of the setting of DisableLLVMLoopOpt.)
1075 const bool do_loop_opt = !get_target().has_feature(Target::DisableLLVMLoopOpt) ||
1076 get_target().has_feature(Target::EnableLLVMLoopOpt);
1077
1078 PipelineTuningOptions pto;
1079 pto.LoopInterleaving = do_loop_opt;
1080 pto.LoopVectorization = do_loop_opt;
1081 pto.SLPVectorization = true; // Note: SLP vectorization has no analogue in the Halide scheduling model
1082 pto.LoopUnrolling = do_loop_opt;
1083 // Clear ScEv info for all loops. Certain Halide applications spend a very
1084 // long time compiling in forgetLoop, and prefer to forget everything
1085 // and rebuild SCEV (aka "Scalar Evolution") from scratch.
1086 // Sample difference in compile time reduction at the time of this change was
1087 // 21.04 -> 14.78 using current ToT release build. (See also https://reviews.llvm.org/rL358304)
1088 pto.ForgetAllSCEVInLoopUnroll = true;
1089
1090#if LLVM_VERSION >= 130
1091 llvm::PassBuilder pb(tm.get(), pto);
1092#elif LLVM_VERSION >= 120
1093 llvm::PassBuilder pb(/*DebugLogging*/ false, tm.get(), pto);
1094#else
1095 llvm::PassBuilder pb(tm.get(), pto);
1096#endif
1097
1098 bool debug_pass_manager = false;
1099 // These analysis managers have to be declared in this order.
1100#if LLVM_VERSION >= 130
1101 llvm::LoopAnalysisManager lam;
1102 llvm::FunctionAnalysisManager fam;
1103 llvm::CGSCCAnalysisManager cgam;
1104 llvm::ModuleAnalysisManager mam;
1105#else
1106 llvm::LoopAnalysisManager lam(debug_pass_manager);
1107 llvm::FunctionAnalysisManager fam(debug_pass_manager);
1108 llvm::CGSCCAnalysisManager cgam(debug_pass_manager);
1109 llvm::ModuleAnalysisManager mam(debug_pass_manager);
1110#endif
1111
1112 llvm::AAManager aa = pb.buildDefaultAAPipeline();
1113 fam.registerPass([&] { return std::move(aa); });
1114
1115 // Register all the basic analyses with the managers.
1116 pb.registerModuleAnalyses(mam);
1117 pb.registerCGSCCAnalyses(cgam);
1118 pb.registerFunctionAnalyses(fam);
1119 pb.registerLoopAnalyses(lam);
1120 pb.crossRegisterProxies(lam, fam, cgam, mam);
1121#if LLVM_VERSION >= 130
1122 ModulePassManager mpm;
1123#else
1124 ModulePassManager mpm(debug_pass_manager);
1125#endif
1126
1127 PassBuilder::OptimizationLevel level = PassBuilder::OptimizationLevel::O3;
1128
1129 if (get_target().has_feature(Target::ASAN)) {
1130#if LLVM_VERSION >= 120
1131 pb.registerPipelineStartEPCallback([&](ModulePassManager &mpm,
1132 PassBuilder::OptimizationLevel) {
1133 mpm.addPass(
1134 RequireAnalysisPass<ASanGlobalsMetadataAnalysis, llvm::Module>());
1135 });
1136#else
1137 pb.registerPipelineStartEPCallback([&](ModulePassManager &mpm) {
1138 mpm.addPass(
1139 RequireAnalysisPass<ASanGlobalsMetadataAnalysis, llvm::Module>());
1140 });
1141#endif
1142 pb.registerOptimizerLastEPCallback(
1143 [](ModulePassManager &mpm, PassBuilder::OptimizationLevel level) {
1144 constexpr bool compile_kernel = false;
1145 constexpr bool recover = false;
1146 constexpr bool use_after_scope = true;
1147 mpm.addPass(createModuleToFunctionPassAdaptor(AddressSanitizerPass(
1148 compile_kernel, recover, use_after_scope)));
1149 });
1150#if LLVM_VERSION >= 120
1151 pb.registerPipelineStartEPCallback(
1152 [](ModulePassManager &mpm, PassBuilder::OptimizationLevel) {
1153 constexpr bool compile_kernel = false;
1154 constexpr bool recover = false;
1155 constexpr bool module_use_after_scope = false;
1156 constexpr bool use_odr_indicator = true;
1157 mpm.addPass(ModuleAddressSanitizerPass(
1158 compile_kernel, recover, module_use_after_scope,
1159 use_odr_indicator));
1160 });
1161#else
1162 pb.registerPipelineStartEPCallback(
1163 [](ModulePassManager &mpm) {
1164 constexpr bool compile_kernel = false;
1165 constexpr bool recover = false;
1166 constexpr bool module_use_after_scope = false;
1167 constexpr bool use_odr_indicator = true;
1168 mpm.addPass(ModuleAddressSanitizerPass(
1169 compile_kernel, recover, module_use_after_scope,
1170 use_odr_indicator));
1171 });
1172#endif
1173 }
1174
1175 if (get_target().has_feature(Target::TSAN)) {
1176 pb.registerOptimizerLastEPCallback(
1177 [](ModulePassManager &mpm, PassBuilder::OptimizationLevel level) {
1178 mpm.addPass(
1179 createModuleToFunctionPassAdaptor(ThreadSanitizerPass()));
1180 });
1181 }
1182
1183 for (llvm::Module::iterator i = module->begin(); i != module->end(); i++) {
1184 if (get_target().has_feature(Target::ASAN)) {
1185 i->addFnAttr(Attribute::SanitizeAddress);
1186 }
1187 if (get_target().has_feature(Target::TSAN)) {
1188 // Do not annotate any of Halide's low-level synchronization code as it has
1189 // tsan interface calls to mark its behavior and is much faster if
1190 // it is not analyzed instruction by instruction.
1191 if (!(i->getName().startswith("_ZN6Halide7Runtime8Internal15Synchronization") ||
1192 // TODO: this is a benign data race that re-initializes the detected features;
1193 // we should really fix it properly inside the implementation, rather than disabling
1194 // it here as a band-aid.
1195 i->getName().startswith("halide_default_can_use_target_features") ||
1196 i->getName().startswith("halide_mutex_") ||
1197 i->getName().startswith("halide_cond_"))) {
1198 i->addFnAttr(Attribute::SanitizeThread);
1199 }
1200 }
1201 }
1202
1203#if LLVM_VERSION >= 130
1204 if (tm) {
1205 tm->registerPassBuilderCallbacks(pb);
1206 }
1207#elif LLVM_VERSION >= 120
1208 if (tm) {
1209 tm->registerPassBuilderCallbacks(pb, debug_pass_manager);
1210 }
1211#endif
1212
1213 mpm = pb.buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline(level, debug_pass_manager);
1214 mpm.run(*module, mam);
1215
1216 if (llvm::verifyModule(*module, &errs())) {
1217 report_fatal_error("Transformation resulted in an invalid module\n");
1218 }
1219
1220 debug(3) << "After LLVM optimizations:\n";
1221 if (debug::debug_level() >= 2) {
1222 module->print(dbgs(), nullptr, false, true);
1223 }
1224
1225 auto *logger = get_compiler_logger();
1226 if (logger) {
1227 auto time_end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
1228 std::chrono::duration<double> diff = time_end - time_start;
1229 logger->record_compilation_time(CompilerLogger::Phase::LLVM, diff.count());
1230 }
1231}

1244llvm::Value *CodeGen_LLVM::sym_get(const string &name, bool must_succeed) const {
1245 // look in the symbol table

1247 if (must_succeed) {

1253 << symbol_table << "\n";

1267
1268Value *CodeGen_LLVM::codegen(const Expr &e) {
1269 internal_assert(e.defined());
1270 debug(4) << "Codegen: " << e.type() << ", " << e << "\n";
1271 value = nullptr;
1272 e.accept(this);
1273 internal_assert(value) << "Codegen of an expr did not produce an llvm value\n"
1274 << e;
1275
1276 // Halide's type system doesn't distinguish between scalars and
1277 // vectors of size 1, so if a codegen method returned a vector of
1278 // size one, just extract it out as a scalar.
1279 if (e.type().is_scalar() &&
1280 value->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
1281 internal_assert(get_vector_num_elements(value->getType()) == 1);
1282 value = builder->CreateExtractElement(value, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0));
1283 }
1284
1285 // TODO: skip this correctness check for bool vectors,
1286 // as eliminate_bool_vectors() will cause a discrepancy for some backends
1287 // (eg OpenCL, HVX, WASM); for now we're just ignoring the assert, but
1288 // in the long run we should improve the smarts. See https://github.com/halide/Halide/issues/4194.
1289 const bool is_bool_vector = e.type().is_bool() && e.type().lanes() > 1;
1290 // TODO: skip this correctness check for prefetch, because the return type
1291 // of prefetch indicates the type being prefetched, which does not match the
1292 // implementation of prefetch.
1293 // See https://github.com/halide/Halide/issues/4211.
1294 const bool is_prefetch = Call::as_intrinsic(e, {Call::prefetch});
1295 internal_assert(is_bool_vector || is_prefetch ||
1296 e.type().is_handle() ||
1297 value->getType()->isVoidTy() ||
1298 value->getType() == llvm_type_of(e.type()))
1299 << "Codegen of Expr " << e
1300 << " of type " << e.type()
1301 << " did not produce llvm IR of the corresponding llvm type.\n";
1302 return value;
1303}

1305void CodeGen_LLVM::codegen(const Stmt &s) {
1306 internal_assert(s.defined());
1307 debug(4) << "Codegen: " << s << "\n";
1308 value = nullptr;
1309 s.accept(this);
1310}

1313bool is_power_of_two(int x) {
1314 return (x & (x - 1)) == 0;
1315}
1316
1317int next_power_of_two(int x) {
1318 return static_cast<int>(1) << static_cast<int>(std::ceil(std::log2(x)));
1319}

1323Type CodeGen_LLVM::upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(const Type &t) const {
1324 if (t.is_bfloat() || (t.is_float() && t.bits() < 32)) {
1325 return Float(32, t.lanes());
1326 } else if (t.is_int_or_uint() && !is_power_of_two(t.bits())) {
1327 return t.with_bits(next_power_of_two(t.bits()));
1328 } else {
1329 return t;
1330 }
1331}
1332
1333Type CodeGen_LLVM::upgrade_type_for_argument_passing(const Type &t) const {
1334 if (t.is_bfloat() || (t.is_float() && t.bits() < 32)) {
1335 return t.with_code(halide_type_uint);
1336 } else {
1337 return t;
1338 }
1339}
1340
1341Type CodeGen_LLVM::upgrade_type_for_storage(const Type &t) const {
1342 if (t.is_bfloat() || (t.is_float() && t.bits() < 32)) {
1343 return t.with_code(halide_type_uint);
1344 } else if (t.is_bool()) {
1345 return t.with_bits(8);
1346 } else if (t.is_handle()) {
1347 return UInt(64, t.lanes());
1348 } else if (t.is_int_or_uint() && !is_power_of_two(t.bits())) {
1349 return t.with_bits(next_power_of_two(t.bits()));
1350 } else {
1351 return t;
1352 }
1353}

1366 } else if (op->type.bits() == 16) {
1367 codegen(reinterpret(Float(16), make_const(UInt(16), float16_t(op->value).to_bits())));

1377void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Cast *op) {
1378 Halide::Type src = op->value.type();
1379 Halide::Type dst = op->type;
1380
1381 if (upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(src) != src ||
1382 upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(dst) != dst) {
1383 // Handle casts to and from types for which we don't have native support.
1384 debug(4) << "Emulating cast from " << src << " to " << dst << "\n";
1385 if ((src.is_float() && src.bits() < 32) ||
1386 (dst.is_float() && dst.bits() < 32)) {
1387 Expr equiv = lower_float16_cast(op);
1388 internal_assert(equiv.type() == op->type);
1389 codegen(equiv);
1390 } else {
1391 internal_error << "Cast from type: " << src
1392 << " to " << dst
1393 << " unimplemented\n";
1394 }
1395 return;
1396 }
1397
1398 value = codegen(op->value);
1399 llvm::Type *llvm_dst = llvm_type_of(dst);
1400
1401 if (dst.is_handle() && src.is_handle()) {
1402 value = builder->CreateBitCast(value, llvm_dst);
1403 } else if (dst.is_handle() || src.is_handle()) {
1404 internal_error << "Can't cast from " << src << " to " << dst << "\n";
1405 } else if (!src.is_float() && !dst.is_float()) {
1406 // Widening integer casts either zero extend or sign extend,
1407 // depending on the source type. Narrowing integer casts
1408 // always truncate.
1409 value = builder->CreateIntCast(value, llvm_dst, src.is_int());
1410 } else if (src.is_float() && dst.is_int()) {
1411 value = builder->CreateFPToSI(value, llvm_dst);
1412 } else if (src.is_float() && dst.is_uint()) {
1413 // fptoui has undefined behavior on overflow. Seems reasonable
1414 // to get an unspecified uint on overflow, but because uint1s
1415 // are stored in uint8s for float->uint1 casts this undefined
1416 // behavior manifests itself as uint1 values greater than 1,
1417 // which could in turn break our bounds inference
1418 // guarantees. So go via uint8 in this case.
1419 if (dst.bits() < 8) {
1420 value = builder->CreateFPToUI(value, llvm_type_of(dst.with_bits(8)));
1421 value = builder->CreateIntCast(value, llvm_dst, false);
1422 } else {
1423 value = builder->CreateFPToUI(value, llvm_dst);
1424 }
1425 } else if (src.is_int() && dst.is_float()) {
1426 value = builder->CreateSIToFP(value, llvm_dst);
1427 } else if (src.is_uint() && dst.is_float()) {
1428 value = builder->CreateUIToFP(value, llvm_dst);
1429 } else {
1430 internal_assert(src.is_float() && dst.is_float());
1431 // Float widening or narrowing
1432 value = builder->CreateFPCast(value, llvm_dst);
1433 }
1434}

1437 value = sym_get(op->name);

1440template<typename Op>
1441bool CodeGen_LLVM::try_to_fold_vector_reduce(const Expr &a, Expr b) {
1442 const VectorReduce *red = a.as<VectorReduce>();
1443 if (!red) {
1444 red = b.as<VectorReduce>();
1445 b = a;
1446 }
1447 if (red &&
1448 ((std::is_same<Op, Add>::value && red->op == VectorReduce::Add) ||
1449 (std::is_same<Op, Min>::value && red->op == VectorReduce::Min) ||
1450 (std::is_same<Op, Max>::value && red->op == VectorReduce::Max) ||
1451 (std::is_same<Op, Mul>::value && red->op == VectorReduce::Mul) ||
1452 (std::is_same<Op, And>::value && red->op == VectorReduce::And) ||
1453 (std::is_same<Op, Or>::value && red->op == VectorReduce::Or) ||
1454 (std::is_same<Op, Call>::value && red->op == VectorReduce::SaturatingAdd))) {
1455 codegen_vector_reduce(red, b);
1456 return true;
1457 }
1458 return false;
1459}
1460
1461void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Add *op) {
1462 Type t = upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(op->type);
1463 if (t != op->type) {
1464 codegen(cast(op->type, Add::make(cast(t, op->a), cast(t, op->b))));
1465 return;
1466 }
1467
1468 // Some backends can fold the add into a vector reduce
1469 if (try_to_fold_vector_reduce<Add>(op->a, op->b)) {
1470 return;
1471 }
1472
1473 Value *a = codegen(op->a);
1474 Value *b = codegen(op->b);
1475 if (op->type.is_float()) {
1476 value = builder->CreateFAdd(a, b);
1477 } else if (op->type.is_int() && op->type.bits() >= 32) {
1478 // We tell llvm integers don't wrap, so that it generates good
1479 // code for loop indices.
1480 value = builder->CreateNSWAdd(a, b);
1481 } else {
1482 value = builder->CreateAdd(a, b);
1483 }
1484}

1495 if (op->type.is_float()) {
1496 value = builder->CreateFSub(a, b);
1497 } else if (op->type.is_int() && op->type.bits() >= 32) {

1530void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Div *op) {
1531 user_assert(!is_const_zero(op->b)) << "Division by constant zero in expression: " << Expr(op) << "\n";
1532
1533 Type t = upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(op->type);
1534 if (t != op->type) {
1535 codegen(cast(op->type, Div::make(cast(t, op->a), cast(t, op->b))));
1536 return;
1537 }
1538
1539 if (op->type.is_float()) {
1540 // Don't call codegen() multiple times within an argument list:
1541 // order-of-evaluation isn't guaranteed and can vary by compiler,
1542 // leading to different LLVM IR ordering, which makes comparing
1543 // output hard.
1544 Value *a = codegen(op->a);
1545 Value *b = codegen(op->b);
1546 value = builder->CreateFDiv(a, b);
1547 } else {
1548 value = codegen(lower_int_uint_div(op->a, op->b));
1549 }
1550}
1551
1552void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Mod *op) {
1553 Type t = upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(op->type);
1554 if (t != op->type) {
1555 codegen(cast(op->type, Mod::make(cast(t, op->a), cast(t, op->b))));
1556 return;
1557 }
1558
1559 if (op->type.is_float()) {
1560 value = codegen(simplify(op->a - op->b * floor(op->a / op->b)));
1561 } else {
1562 value = codegen(lower_int_uint_mod(op->a, op->b));
1563 }
1564}

1566void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Min *op) {
1567 Type t = upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(op->type);
1568 if (t != op->type) {
1569 codegen(cast(op->type, Min::make(cast(t, op->a), cast(t, op->b))));
1570 return;
1571 }
1572
1573 if (try_to_fold_vector_reduce<Min>(op->a, op->b)) {
1574 return;
1575 }
1576
1577 string a_name = unique_name('a');
1578 string b_name = unique_name('b');
1579 Expr a = Variable::make(op->a.type(), a_name);
1580 Expr b = Variable::make(op->b.type(), b_name);
1581 value = codegen(Let::make(a_name, op->a,
1582 Let::make(b_name, op->b,
1583 select(a < b, a, b))));
1584}

1743namespace {
1744Expr promote_64(const Expr &e) {
1745 if (const Add *a = e.as<Add>()) {
1746 return Add::make(promote_64(a->a), promote_64(a->b));
1747 } else if (const Sub *s = e.as<Sub>()) {
1748 return Sub::make(promote_64(s->a), promote_64(s->b));
1749 } else if (const Mul *m = e.as<Mul>()) {
1750 return Mul::make(promote_64(m->a), promote_64(m->b));
1751 } else if (const Min *m = e.as<Min>()) {
1752 return Min::make(promote_64(m->a), promote_64(m->b));
1753 } else if (const Max *m = e.as<Max>()) {
1754 return Max::make(promote_64(m->a), promote_64(m->b));
1755 } else {
1756 return cast(Int(64), e);
1757 }
1758}

1766
1767Value *CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_buffer_pointer(Value *base_address, Halide::Type type, Expr index) {
1768 // Promote index to 64-bit on targets that use 64-bit pointers.
1769 llvm::DataLayout d(module.get());
1770 if (promote_indices() && d.getPointerSize() == 8) {
1771 index = promote_64(index);
1772 }
1773
1774 // Peel off a constant offset as a second GEP. This helps LLVM's
1775 // aliasing analysis, especially for backends that do address
1776 // computation in 32 bits but use 64-bit pointers.
1777 if (const Add *add = index.as<Add>()) {
1778 if (const int64_t *offset = as_const_int(add->b)) {
1779 Value *base = codegen_buffer_pointer(base_address, type, add->a);
1780 Value *off = codegen(make_const(Int(8 * d.getPointerSize()), *offset));
1781 return builder->CreateInBoundsGEP(base, off);
1782 }
1783 }
1784
1785 return codegen_buffer_pointer(base_address, type, codegen(index));
1786}

1794Value *CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_buffer_pointer(Value *base_address, Halide::Type type, Value *index) {
1795 llvm::Type *base_address_type = base_address->getType();
1796 unsigned address_space = base_address_type->getPointerAddressSpace();
1797
1798 type = upgrade_type_for_storage(type);
1799
1800 llvm::Type *load_type = llvm_type_of(type)->getPointerTo(address_space);
1801
1802 // If the type doesn't match the expected type, we need to pointer cast
1803 if (load_type != base_address_type) {
1804 base_address = builder->CreatePointerCast(base_address, load_type);
1805 }
1806
1807 llvm::Constant *constant_index = dyn_cast<llvm::Constant>(index);
1808 if (constant_index && constant_index->isZeroValue()) {
1809 return base_address;
1810 }
1811
1812 // Promote index to 64-bit on targets that use 64-bit pointers.
1813 llvm::DataLayout d(module.get());
1814 if (d.getPointerSize() == 8) {
1815 index = builder->CreateIntCast(index, i64_t, true);
1816 }
1817
1818 return builder->CreateInBoundsGEP(base_address, index);
1819}

1821void CodeGen_LLVM::add_tbaa_metadata(llvm::Instruction *inst, string buffer, const Expr &index) {
1822
1823 // Get the unique name for the block of memory this allocate node
1824 // is using.
1825 buffer = get_allocation_name(buffer);
1826
1827 // If the index is constant, we generate some TBAA info that helps
1828 // LLVM understand our loads/stores aren't aliased.
1829 bool constant_index = false;
1830 int64_t base = 0;
1831 int64_t width = 1;
1832
1833 if (index.defined()) {
1834 if (const Ramp *ramp = index.as<Ramp>()) {
1835 const int64_t *pstride = as_const_int(ramp->stride);
1836 const int64_t *pbase = as_const_int(ramp->base);
1837 if (pstride && pbase) {
1838 // We want to find the smallest aligned width and offset
1839 // that contains this ramp.
1840 int64_t stride = *pstride;
1841 base = *pbase;
1842 internal_assert(base >= 0);
1843 width = next_power_of_two(ramp->lanes * stride);
1844
1845 while (base % width) {
1846 base -= base % width;
1847 width *= 2;
1848 }
1849 constant_index = true;
1850 }
1851 } else {
1852 const int64_t *pbase = as_const_int(index);
1853 if (pbase) {
1854 base = *pbase;
1855 constant_index = true;
1856 }
1857 }
1858 }
1859
1860 llvm::MDBuilder builder(*context);
1861
1862 // Add type-based-alias-analysis metadata to the pointer, so that
1863 // loads and stores to different buffers can get reordered.
1864 MDNode *tbaa = builder.createTBAARoot("Halide buffer");
1865
1866 tbaa = builder.createTBAAScalarTypeNode(buffer, tbaa);
1867
1868 // We also add metadata for constant indices to allow loads and
1869 // stores to the same buffer to get reordered.
1870 if (constant_index) {
1871 for (int w = 1024; w >= width; w /= 2) {
1872 int64_t b = (base / w) * w;
1873
1874 std::stringstream level;
1875 level << buffer << ".width" << w << ".base" << b;
1876 tbaa = builder.createTBAAScalarTypeNode(level.str(), tbaa);
1877 }
1878 }
1879
1880 tbaa = builder.createTBAAStructTagNode(tbaa, tbaa, 0);
1881
1882 inst->setMetadata("tbaa", tbaa);
1883}

1885void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Load *op) {
1886 // If the type should be stored as some other type, insert a reinterpret cast.
1887 Type storage_type = upgrade_type_for_storage(op->type);
1888 if (op->type != storage_type) {
1889 codegen(reinterpret(op->type, Load::make(storage_type, op->name,
1890 op->index, op->image,
1891 op->param, op->predicate, op->alignment)));
1892 return;
1893 }
1894
1895 // Predicated load
1896 if (!is_const_one(op->predicate)) {
1897 codegen_predicated_vector_load(op);
1898 return;
1899 }
1900
1901 // There are several cases. Different architectures may wish to override some.
1902 if (op->type.is_scalar()) {
1903 // Scalar loads
1904 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, op->type, op->index);
1905 LoadInst *load = builder->CreateAlignedLoad(ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), ptr, llvm::Align(op->type.bytes()));
1906 add_tbaa_metadata(load, op->name, op->index);
1907 value = load;
1908 } else {
1909 const Ramp *ramp = op->index.as<Ramp>();
1910 const IntImm *stride = ramp ? ramp->stride.as<IntImm>() : nullptr;
1911
1912 if (ramp && stride && stride->value == 1) {
1913 value = codegen_dense_vector_load(op);
1914 } else if (ramp && stride && 2 <= stride->value && stride->value <= 4) {
1915 // Try to rewrite strided loads as shuffles of dense loads,
1916 // aligned to the stride. This makes adjacent strided loads
1917 // share the same underlying dense loads.
1918 Expr base = ramp->base;
1919 // The variable align will track the alignment of the
1920 // base. Every time we change base, we also need to update
1921 // align.
1922 ModulusRemainder align = op->alignment;
1923
1924 int aligned_stride = gcd(stride->value, align.modulus);
1925 int offset = 0;
1926 if (aligned_stride == stride->value) {
1927 offset = mod_imp((int)align.remainder, aligned_stride);
1928 } else {
1929 const Add *add = base.as<Add>();
1930 if (const IntImm *add_c = add ? add->b.as<IntImm>() : base.as<IntImm>()) {
1931 offset = mod_imp(add_c->value, stride->value);
1932 }
1933 }
1934
1935 if (offset) {
1936 base = simplify(base - offset);
1937 align.remainder = mod_imp(align.remainder - offset, align.modulus);
1938 }
1939
1940 // We want to load a few more bytes than the original load did.
1941 // We know this is safe for internal buffers because we allocate
1942 // padding.
1943 // (In ASAN mode, don't read beyond the end of internal buffers either,
1944 // as ASAN will complain even about harmless stack overreads.)
1945 // The min moves lower by offset.
1946 int load_lanes = ramp->lanes * stride->value;
1947 bool external = op->param.defined() || op->image.defined();
1948 if (external || target.has_feature(Target::ASAN)) {
1949 load_lanes -= (stride->value - 1 - offset);
1950 }
1951
1952 int slice_lanes = native_vector_bits() / op->type.bits();
1953
1954 // We're going to add multiples of slice_lanes to base in
1955 // the loop below, so reduce alignment modulo slice_lanes.
1956 align.modulus = gcd(align.modulus, slice_lanes);
1957 align.remainder = mod_imp(align.remainder, align.modulus);
1958
1959 // We need to slice the result in to native vector lanes, otherwise
1960 // LLVM misses optimizations like using ldN on ARM.
1961 vector<Value *> results;
1962 for (int i = 0; i < op->type.lanes(); i += slice_lanes) {
1963 int load_base_i = i * stride->value;
1964 int load_lanes_i = std::min<int>(slice_lanes * stride->value, load_lanes - load_base_i);
1965 int lanes_i = std::min<int>(slice_lanes, op->type.lanes() - i);
1966 Expr slice_base = simplify(base + load_base_i);
1967
1968 Value *load_i = codegen_dense_vector_load(op->type.with_lanes(load_lanes_i), op->name, slice_base,
1969 op->image, op->param, align, nullptr, false);
1970
1971 SmallVector<Constant *, 256> constants;
1972 for (int j = 0; j < lanes_i; j++) {
1973 Constant *constant = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, j * stride->value + offset);
1974 constants.push_back(constant);
1975 }
1976 Constant *constantsV = ConstantVector::get(constants);
1977 Value *undef = UndefValue::get(load_i->getType());
1978 Value *shuffleInstr = builder->CreateShuffleVector(load_i, undef, constantsV);
1979 results.push_back(shuffleInstr);
1980 }
1981
1982 // Concat the results
1983 value = concat_vectors(results);
1984 } else if (ramp && stride && stride->value == -1) {
1985 // Load the vector and then flip it in-place
1986 Expr flipped_base = ramp->base - ramp->lanes + 1;
1987 Expr flipped_stride = make_one(flipped_base.type());
1988 Expr flipped_index = Ramp::make(flipped_base, flipped_stride, ramp->lanes);
1989 ModulusRemainder align = op->alignment;
1990 // Switch to the alignment of the last lane
1991 align = align - (ramp->lanes - 1);
1992 Expr flipped_load = Load::make(op->type, op->name, flipped_index, op->image, op->param, op->predicate, align);
1993
1994 Value *flipped = codegen(flipped_load);
1995
1996 vector<int> indices(ramp->lanes);
1997 for (int i = 0; i < ramp->lanes; i++) {
1998 indices[i] = ramp->lanes - 1 - i;
1999 }
2000
2001 value = shuffle_vectors(flipped, indices);
2002 } else if (ramp) {
2003 // Gather without generating the indices as a vector
2004 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, op->type.element_of(), ramp->base);
2005 Value *stride = codegen(ramp->stride);
2006 value = UndefValue::get(llvm_type_of(op->type));
2007 for (int i = 0; i < ramp->lanes; i++) {
2008 Value *lane = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i);
2009 LoadInst *val = builder->CreateLoad(ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), ptr);
2010 add_tbaa_metadata(val, op->name, op->index);
2011 value = builder->CreateInsertElement(value, val, lane);
2012 ptr = builder->CreateInBoundsGEP(ptr, stride);
2013 }
2014 } else if ((false)) { /* should_scalarize(op->index) */
2015 // TODO: put something sensible in for
2016 // should_scalarize. Probably a good idea if there are no
2017 // loads in it, and it's all int32.
2018
2019 // Compute the index as scalars, and then do a gather
2020 Value *vec = UndefValue::get(llvm_type_of(op->type));
2021 for (int i = 0; i < op->type.lanes(); i++) {
2022 Expr idx = extract_lane(op->index, i);
2023 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, op->type.element_of(), idx);
2024 LoadInst *val = builder->CreateLoad(ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), ptr);
2025 add_tbaa_metadata(val, op->name, op->index);
2026 vec = builder->CreateInsertElement(vec, val, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i));
2027 }
2028 value = vec;
2029 } else {
2030 // General gathers
2031 Value *index = codegen(op->index);
2032 Value *vec = UndefValue::get(llvm_type_of(op->type));
2033 for (int i = 0; i < op->type.lanes(); i++) {
2034 Value *idx = builder->CreateExtractElement(index, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i));
2035 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, op->type.element_of(), idx);
2036 LoadInst *val = builder->CreateLoad(ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), ptr);
2037 add_tbaa_metadata(val, op->name, op->index);
2038 vec = builder->CreateInsertElement(vec, val, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i));
2039 }
2040 value = vec;
2041 }
2042 }
2043}

2045void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Ramp *op) {
2046 if (is_const(op->stride) && !is_const(op->base)) {
2047 // If the stride is const and the base is not (e.g. ramp(x, 1,
2048 // 4)), we can lift out the stride and broadcast the base so
2049 // we can do a single vector broadcast and add instead of
2050 // repeated insertion
2051 Expr broadcast = Broadcast::make(op->base, op->lanes);
2052 Expr ramp = Ramp::make(make_zero(op->base.type()), op->stride, op->lanes);
2053 value = codegen(broadcast + ramp);
2054 } else if (!is_const(op->stride)) {
2055 Expr broadcast_base = Broadcast::make(op->base, op->lanes);
2056 Expr broadcast_stride = Broadcast::make(op->stride, op->lanes);
2057 Expr ramp = Ramp::make(make_zero(op->base.type()), make_one(op->base.type()), op->lanes);
2058 value = codegen(broadcast_base + broadcast_stride * ramp);
2059 } else {
2060 internal_assert(is_const(op->base) && is_const(op->stride));
2061 // At this point base and stride should be constant. Generate
2062 // an insert element sequence. The code will be lifted to a
2063 // constant vector stored in .rodata or similar.
2064 Value *base = codegen(op->base);
2065 Value *stride = codegen(op->stride);
2066
2067 value = UndefValue::get(llvm_type_of(op->type));
2068 for (int i = 0; i < op->type.lanes(); i++) {
2069 if (i > 0) {
2070 if (op->type.is_float()) {
2071 base = builder->CreateFAdd(base, stride);
2072 } else if (op->type.is_int() && op->type.bits() >= 32) {
2073 base = builder->CreateNSWAdd(base, stride);
2074 } else {
2075 base = builder->CreateAdd(base, stride);
2076 }
2077 }
2078 value = builder->CreateInsertElement(value, base, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i));
2079 }
2080 }
2081}

2083llvm::Value *CodeGen_LLVM::create_broadcast(llvm::Value *v, int lanes) {
2084 Constant *undef = UndefValue::get(get_vector_type(v->getType(), lanes));
2085 Constant *zero = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0);
2086 v = builder->CreateInsertElement(undef, v, zero);
2087 Constant *zeros = ConstantVector::getSplat(element_count(lanes), zero);
2088 return builder->CreateShuffleVector(v, undef, zeros);
2089}

2091void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Broadcast *op) {
2092 Value *v = codegen(op->value);
2093 value = create_broadcast(v, op->lanes);
2094}

2096Value *CodeGen_LLVM::interleave_vectors(const std::vector<Value *> &vecs) {
2097 internal_assert(!vecs.empty());
2098 for (size_t i = 1; i < vecs.size(); i++) {
2099 internal_assert(vecs[0]->getType() == vecs[i]->getType());
2100 }
2101 int vec_elements = get_vector_num_elements(vecs[0]->getType());
2102
2103 if (vecs.size() == 1) {
2104 return vecs[0];
2105 } else if (vecs.size() == 2) {
2106 Value *a = vecs[0];
2107 Value *b = vecs[1];
2108 vector<int> indices(vec_elements * 2);
2109 for (int i = 0; i < vec_elements * 2; i++) {
2110 indices[i] = i % 2 == 0 ? i / 2 : i / 2 + vec_elements;
2111 }
2112 return shuffle_vectors(a, b, indices);
2113 } else {
2114 // Grab the even and odd elements of vecs.
2115 vector<Value *> even_vecs;
2116 vector<Value *> odd_vecs;
2117 for (size_t i = 0; i < vecs.size(); i++) {
2118 if (i % 2 == 0) {
2119 even_vecs.push_back(vecs[i]);
2120 } else {
2121 odd_vecs.push_back(vecs[i]);
2122 }
2123 }
2124
2125 // If the number of vecs is odd, save the last one for later.
2126 Value *last = nullptr;
2127 if (even_vecs.size() > odd_vecs.size()) {
2128 last = even_vecs.back();
2129 even_vecs.pop_back();
2130 }
2131 internal_assert(even_vecs.size() == odd_vecs.size());
2132
2133 // Interleave the even and odd parts.
2134 Value *even = interleave_vectors(even_vecs);
2135 Value *odd = interleave_vectors(odd_vecs);
2136
2137 if (last) {
2138 int result_elements = vec_elements * vecs.size();
2139
2140 // Interleave even and odd, leaving a space for the last element.
2141 vector<int> indices(result_elements, -1);
2142 for (int i = 0, idx = 0; i < result_elements; i++) {
2143 if (i % vecs.size() < vecs.size() - 1) {
2144 indices[i] = idx % 2 == 0 ? idx / 2 : idx / 2 + vec_elements * even_vecs.size();
2145 idx++;
2146 }
2147 }
2148 Value *even_odd = shuffle_vectors(even, odd, indices);
2149
2150 // Interleave the last vector into the result.
2151 last = slice_vector(last, 0, result_elements);
2152 for (int i = 0; i < result_elements; i++) {
2153 if (i % vecs.size() < vecs.size() - 1) {
2154 indices[i] = i;
2155 } else {
2156 indices[i] = i / vecs.size() + result_elements;
2157 }
2158 }
2159
2160 return shuffle_vectors(even_odd, last, indices);
2161 } else {
2162 return interleave_vectors({even, odd});
2163 }
2164 }
2165}

2168 llvm::Type *result_type = llvm_type_of(e.type());
2169
2170 Value *result = UndefValue::get(result_type);
2171
2172 for (int i = 0; i < e.type().lanes(); i++) {
2173 Value *v = codegen(extract_lane(e, i));
2174 result = builder->CreateInsertElement(result, v, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i));

2176 value = result;
2177}
