2179void CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_predicated_vector_store(const Store *op) {
2180 const Ramp *ramp = op->index.as<Ramp>();
2181 if (ramp && is_const_one(ramp->stride) && !emit_atomic_stores) { // Dense vector store
2182 debug(4) << "Predicated dense vector store\n\t" << Stmt(op) << "\n";
2183 Value *vpred = codegen(op->predicate);
2184 Halide::Type value_type = op->value.type();
2185 Value *val = codegen(op->value);
2186 bool is_external = (external_buffer.find(op->name) != external_buffer.end());
2187 int alignment = value_type.bytes();
2188 int native_bits = native_vector_bits();
2189 int native_bytes = native_bits / 8;
2190
2191 // Boost the alignment if possible, up to the native vector width.
2192 ModulusRemainder mod_rem = op->alignment;
2193 while ((mod_rem.remainder & 1) == 0 &&
2194 (mod_rem.modulus & 1) == 0 &&
2195 alignment < native_bytes) {
2196 mod_rem.modulus /= 2;
2197 mod_rem.remainder /= 2;
2198 alignment *= 2;
2199 }
2200
2201 // If it is an external buffer, then we cannot assume that the host pointer
2202 // is aligned to at least the native vector width. However, we may be able to do
2203 // better than just assuming that it is unaligned.
2204 if (is_external && op->param.defined()) {
2205 int host_alignment = op->param.host_alignment();
2206 alignment = gcd(alignment, host_alignment);
2207 }
2208
2209 // For dense vector stores wider than the native vector
2210 // width, bust them up into native vectors.
2211 int store_lanes = value_type.lanes();
2212 int native_lanes = native_bits / value_type.bits();
2213
2214 for (int i = 0; i < store_lanes; i += native_lanes) {
2215 int slice_lanes = std::min(native_lanes, store_lanes - i);
2216 Expr slice_base = simplify(ramp->base + i);
2217 Expr slice_stride = make_one(slice_base.type());
2218 Expr slice_index = slice_lanes == 1 ? slice_base : Ramp::make(slice_base, slice_stride, slice_lanes);
2219 Value *slice_val = slice_vector(val, i, slice_lanes);
2220 Value *elt_ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type.element_of(), slice_base);
2221 Value *vec_ptr = builder->CreatePointerCast(elt_ptr, slice_val->getType()->getPointerTo());
2222
2223 Value *slice_mask = slice_vector(vpred, i, slice_lanes);
2224 Instruction *store =
2225 builder->CreateMaskedStore(slice_val, vec_ptr, llvm::Align(alignment), slice_mask);
2226 add_tbaa_metadata(store, op->name, slice_index);
2227 }
2228 } else { // It's not dense vector store, we need to scalarize it
2229 debug(4) << "Scalarize predicated vector store\n";
2230 Type value_type = op->value.type().element_of();
2231 Value *vpred = codegen(op->predicate);
2232 Value *vval = codegen(op->value);
2233 Value *vindex = codegen(op->index);
2234 for (int i = 0; i < op->index.type().lanes(); i++) {
2235 Constant *lane = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i);
2236 Value *p = builder->CreateExtractElement(vpred, lane);
2237 if (p->getType() != i1_t) {
2238 p = builder->CreateIsNotNull(p);
2239 }
2240
2241 Value *v = builder->CreateExtractElement(vval, lane);
2242 Value *idx = builder->CreateExtractElement(vindex, lane);
2243 internal_assert(p && v && idx);
2244
2245 BasicBlock *true_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "true_bb", function);
2246 BasicBlock *after_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "after_bb", function);
2247 builder->CreateCondBr(p, true_bb, after_bb);
2248
2249 builder->SetInsertPoint(true_bb);
2250
2251 // Scalar
2252 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type, idx);
2253 StoreInst *store = builder->CreateAlignedStore(v, ptr, llvm::Align(value_type.bytes()));
2254 if (emit_atomic_stores) {
2255 store->setAtomic(AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2256 }
2257
2258 builder->CreateBr(after_bb);
2259 builder->SetInsertPoint(after_bb);
2260 }
2261 }
2262}
2263
2264llvm::Value *CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_dense_vector_load(const Type &type, const std::string &name, const Expr &base,
2265 const Buffer<> &image, const Parameter &param, const ModulusRemainder &alignment,
2266 llvm::Value *vpred, bool slice_to_native) {
2267 debug(4) << "Vectorize predicated dense vector load:\n\t"
2268 << "(" << type << ")" << name << "[ramp(base, 1, " << type.lanes() << ")]\n";
2269
2270 bool is_external = (external_buffer.find(name) != external_buffer.end());
2271 int align_bytes = type.bytes(); // The size of a single element
2272
2273 int native_bits = native_vector_bits();
2274 int native_bytes = native_bits / 8;
2275
2276 // We assume halide_malloc for the platform returns buffers
2277 // aligned to at least the native vector width. So this is the
2278 // maximum alignment we can infer based on the index alone.
2279
2280 // Boost the alignment if possible, up to the native vector width.
2281 ModulusRemainder mod_rem = alignment;
2282 while ((mod_rem.remainder & 1) == 0 &&
2283 (mod_rem.modulus & 1) == 0 &&
2284 align_bytes < native_bytes) {
2285 mod_rem.modulus /= 2;
2286 mod_rem.remainder /= 2;
2287 align_bytes *= 2;
2288 }
2289
2290 // If it is an external buffer, then we cannot assume that the host pointer
2291 // is aligned to at least native vector width. However, we may be able to do
2292 // better than just assuming that it is unaligned.
2293 if (is_external) {
2294 if (param.defined()) {
2295 int host_alignment = param.host_alignment();
2296 align_bytes = gcd(align_bytes, host_alignment);
2297 } else if (get_target().has_feature(Target::JIT) && image.defined()) {
2298 // If we're JITting, use the actual pointer value to determine alignment for embedded buffers.
2299 align_bytes = gcd(align_bytes, (int)(((uintptr_t)image.data()) & std::numeric_limits<int>::max()));
2300 }
2301 }
2302
2303 // For dense vector loads wider than the native vector
2304 // width, bust them up into native vectors
2305 int load_lanes = type.lanes();
2306 int native_lanes = slice_to_native ? std::max(1, native_bits / type.bits()) : load_lanes;
2307 vector<Value *> slices;
2308 for (int i = 0; i < load_lanes; i += native_lanes) {
2309 int slice_lanes = std::min(native_lanes, load_lanes - i);
2310 Expr slice_base = simplify(base + i);
2311 Expr slice_stride = make_one(slice_base.type());
2312 Expr slice_index = slice_lanes == 1 ? slice_base : Ramp::make(slice_base, slice_stride, slice_lanes);
2313 llvm::Type *slice_type = get_vector_type(llvm_type_of(type.element_of()), slice_lanes);
2314 Value *elt_ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(name, type.element_of(), slice_base);
2315 Value *vec_ptr = builder->CreatePointerCast(elt_ptr, slice_type->getPointerTo());
2316
2317 Instruction *load_inst;
2318 if (vpred != nullptr) {
2319 Value *slice_mask = slice_vector(vpred, i, slice_lanes);
2320 load_inst = builder->CreateMaskedLoad(vec_ptr, llvm::Align(align_bytes), slice_mask);
2321 } else {
2322 load_inst = builder->CreateAlignedLoad(vec_ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), vec_ptr, llvm::Align(align_bytes));
2323 }
2324 add_tbaa_metadata(load_inst, name, slice_index);
2325 slices.push_back(load_inst);
2326 }
2327 value = concat_vectors(slices);
2328 return value;
2329}
2330
2331Value *CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_dense_vector_load(const Load *load, Value *vpred, bool slice_to_native) {
2332 const Ramp *ramp = load->index.as<Ramp>();
2333 internal_assert(ramp && is_const_one(ramp->stride)) << "Should be dense vector load\n";
2334
2335 return codegen_dense_vector_load(load->type, load->name, ramp->base, load->image, load->param,
2336 load->alignment, vpred, slice_to_native);
2337}
2338
2339void CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_predicated_vector_load(const Load *op) {
2340 const Ramp *ramp = op->index.as<Ramp>();
2341 const IntImm *stride = ramp ? ramp->stride.as<IntImm>() : nullptr;
2342
2343 if (ramp && is_const_one(ramp->stride)) { // Dense vector load
2344 Value *vpred = codegen(op->predicate);
2345 value = codegen_dense_vector_load(op, vpred);
2346 } else if (ramp && stride && stride->value == -1) {
2347 debug(4) << "Predicated dense vector load with stride -1\n\t" << Expr(op) << "\n";
2348 vector<int> indices(ramp->lanes);
2349 for (int i = 0; i < ramp->lanes; i++) {
2350 indices[i] = ramp->lanes - 1 - i;
2351 }
2352
2353 // Flip the predicate
2354 Value *vpred = codegen(op->predicate);
2355 vpred = shuffle_vectors(vpred, indices);
2356
2357 // Load the vector and then flip it in-place
2358 Expr flipped_base = ramp->base - ramp->lanes + 1;
2359 Expr flipped_stride = make_one(flipped_base.type());
2360 Expr flipped_index = Ramp::make(flipped_base, flipped_stride, ramp->lanes);
2361 ModulusRemainder align = op->alignment;
2362 align = align - (ramp->lanes - 1);
2363
2364 Expr flipped_load = Load::make(op->type, op->name, flipped_index, op->image,
2365 op->param, const_true(op->type.lanes()), align);
2366
2367 Value *flipped = codegen_dense_vector_load(flipped_load.as<Load>(), vpred);
2368 value = shuffle_vectors(flipped, indices);
2369 } else { // It's not dense vector load, we need to scalarize it
2370 Expr load_expr = Load::make(op->type, op->name, op->index, op->image,
2371 op->param, const_true(op->type.lanes()), op->alignment);
2372 debug(4) << "Scalarize predicated vector load\n\t" << load_expr << "\n";
2373 Expr pred_load = Call::make(load_expr.type(),
2374 Call::if_then_else,
2375 {op->predicate, load_expr, make_zero(load_expr.type())},
2376 Internal::Call::Intrinsic);
2377 value = codegen(pred_load);
2378 }
2379}
2380
2381void CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_atomic_rmw(const Store *op) {
2382 // TODO: predicated store (see https://github.com/halide/Halide/issues/4298).
2383 user_assert(is_const_one(op->predicate)) << "Atomic predicated store is not supported.\n";
2384
2385 // Detect whether we can describe this as an atomic-read-modify-write,
2386 // otherwise fallback to a compare-and-swap loop.
2387 // Currently we only test for atomicAdd.
2388 Expr val_expr = op->value;
2389 Halide::Type value_type = op->value.type();
2390
2391 // For atomicAdd, we check if op->value - store[index] is independent of store.
2392 // For llvm version < 9, the atomicRMW operations only support integers so we also check that.
2393 Expr equiv_load = Load::make(value_type, op->name,
2394 op->index,
2395 Buffer<>(),
2396 op->param,
2397 op->predicate,
2398 op->alignment);
2399 Expr delta = simplify(common_subexpression_elimination(op->value - equiv_load));
2400 bool is_atomic_add = supports_atomic_add(value_type) && !expr_uses_var(delta, op->name);
2401 if (is_atomic_add) {
2402 Value *val = codegen(delta);
2403 if (value_type.is_scalar()) {
2404 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name,
2405 op->value.type(),
2406 op->index);
2407#if LLVM_VERSION >= 130
2408 if (value_type.is_float()) {
2409 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::FAdd, ptr, val, llvm::MaybeAlign(), AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2410 } else {
2411 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::Add, ptr, val, llvm::MaybeAlign(), AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2412 }
2413#else
2414 // llvm 9 has FAdd which can be used for atomic floats.
2415 if (value_type.is_float()) {
2416 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::FAdd, ptr, val, AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2417 } else {
2418 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::Add, ptr, val, AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2419 }
2420#endif
2421 } else {
2422 Value *index = codegen(op->index);
2423 // Scalarize vector store.
2424 for (int i = 0; i < value_type.lanes(); i++) {
2425 Value *lane = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i);
2426 Value *idx = builder->CreateExtractElement(index, lane);
2427 Value *v = builder->CreateExtractElement(val, lane);
2428 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type.element_of(), idx);
2429#if LLVM_VERSION >= 130
2430 if (value_type.is_float()) {
2431 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::FAdd, ptr, v, llvm::MaybeAlign(), AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2432 } else {
2433 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::Add, ptr, v, llvm::MaybeAlign(), AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2434 }
2435#else
2436 if (value_type.is_float()) {
2437 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::FAdd, ptr, v, AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2438 } else {
2439 builder->CreateAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst::Add, ptr, v, AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2440 }
2441#endif
2442 }
2443 }
2444 } else {
2445 // We want to create the following CAS loop:
2446 // entry:
2447 // %orig = load atomic op->name[op->index]
2448 // br label %casloop.start
2449 // casloop.start:
2450 // %cmp = phi [%orig, %entry], [%value_loaded %casloop.start]
2451 // %val = ...
2452 // %val_success = cmpxchg %ptr, %cmp, %val, monotonic
2453 // %val_loaded = extractvalue %val_success, 0
2454 // %success = extractvalue %val_success, 1
2455 // br %success, label %casloop.end, label %casloop.start
2456 // casloop.end:
2457 Value *vec_index = nullptr;
2458 if (!value_type.is_scalar()) {
2459 // Precompute index for vector store.
2460 vec_index = codegen(op->index);
2461 }
2462 // Scalarize vector store.
2463 for (int lane_id = 0; lane_id < value_type.lanes(); lane_id++) {
2464 LLVMContext &ctx = builder->getContext();
2465 BasicBlock *bb = builder->GetInsertBlock();
2466 llvm::Function *f = bb->getParent();
2467 BasicBlock *loop_bb =
2468 BasicBlock::Create(ctx, "casloop.start", f);
2469 // Load the old value for compare and swap test.
2470 Value *ptr = nullptr;
2471 if (value_type.is_scalar()) {
2472 ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type, op->index);
2473 } else {
2474 Value *idx = builder->CreateExtractElement(vec_index, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, lane_id));
2475 ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type.element_of(), idx);
2476 }
2477 LoadInst *orig = builder->CreateAlignedLoad(ptr->getType()->getPointerElementType(), ptr, llvm::Align(value_type.bytes()));
2478 orig->setOrdering(AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2479 add_tbaa_metadata(orig, op->name, op->index);
2480 // Explicit fall through from the current block to the cas loop body.
2481 builder->CreateBr(loop_bb);
2482
2483 // CAS loop body:
2484 builder->SetInsertPoint(loop_bb);
2485 llvm::Type *ptr_type = ptr->getType();
2486 PHINode *cmp = builder->CreatePHI(ptr_type->getPointerElementType(), 2, "loaded");
2487 Value *cmp_val = cmp;
2488 cmp->addIncoming(orig, bb);
2489 Value *val = nullptr;
2490 if (value_type.is_scalar()) {
2491 val = codegen(op->value);
2492 } else {
2493 val = codegen(extract_lane(op->value, lane_id));
2494 }
2495 llvm::Type *val_type = val->getType();
2496 bool need_bit_cast = val_type->isFloatingPointTy();
2497 if (need_bit_cast) {
2498 IntegerType *int_type = builder->getIntNTy(val_type->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
2499 unsigned int addr_space = ptr_type->getPointerAddressSpace();
2500 ptr = builder->CreateBitCast(ptr, int_type->getPointerTo(addr_space));
2501 val = builder->CreateBitCast(val, int_type);
2502 cmp_val = builder->CreateBitCast(cmp_val, int_type);
2503 }
2504#if LLVM_VERSION >= 130
2505 Value *cmpxchg_pair = builder->CreateAtomicCmpXchg(
2506 ptr, cmp_val, val, llvm::MaybeAlign(), AtomicOrdering::Monotonic, AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2507#else
2508 Value *cmpxchg_pair = builder->CreateAtomicCmpXchg(
2509 ptr, cmp_val, val, AtomicOrdering::Monotonic, AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
2510#endif
2511 Value *val_loaded = builder->CreateExtractValue(cmpxchg_pair, 0, "val_loaded");
2512 Value *success = builder->CreateExtractValue(cmpxchg_pair, 1, "success");
2513 if (need_bit_cast) {
2514 val_loaded = builder->CreateBitCast(val_loaded, val_type);
2515 }
2516 cmp->addIncoming(val_loaded, loop_bb);
2517 BasicBlock *exit_bb =
2518 BasicBlock::Create(ctx, "casloop.end", f);
2519 builder->CreateCondBr(success, exit_bb, loop_bb);
2520 builder->SetInsertPoint(exit_bb);
2521 }
2522 }
2523}
2524
2525void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Call *op) {
2526 internal_assert(op->is_extern() || op->is_intrinsic())
2527 << "Can only codegen extern calls and intrinsics\n";
2528
2529 if (op->type.is_vector()) {
2530 value = call_overloaded_intrin(op->type, op->name, op->args);
2531 if (value) {
2532 return;
2533 }
2534 }
2535
2536 // Some call nodes are actually injected at various stages as a
2537 // cue for llvm to generate particular ops. In general these are
2538 // handled in the standard library, but ones with e.g. varying
2539 // types are handled here.
2540 if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::debug_to_file)) {
2541 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 3);
2542 const StringImm *filename = op->args[0].as<StringImm>();
2543 internal_assert(filename) << "Malformed debug_to_file node\n";
2544 // Grab the function from the initial module
2545 llvm::Function *debug_to_file = module->getFunction("halide_debug_to_file");
2546 internal_assert(debug_to_file) << "Could not find halide_debug_to_file function in initial module\n";
2547
2548 // Make the filename a global string constant
2549 Value *user_context = get_user_context();
2550 Value *char_ptr = codegen(Expr(filename));
2551 vector<Value *> args = {user_context, char_ptr, codegen(op->args[1])};
2552
2553 Value *buffer = codegen(op->args[2]);
2554 buffer = builder->CreatePointerCast(buffer, debug_to_file->getFunctionType()->getParamType(3));
2555 args.push_back(buffer);
2556
2557 value = builder->CreateCall(debug_to_file, args);
2558
2559 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::bitwise_and)) {
2560 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2561 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2562 Value *b = codegen(op->args[1]);
2563 value = builder->CreateAnd(a, b);
2564 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::bitwise_xor)) {
2565 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2566 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2567 Value *b = codegen(op->args[1]);
2568 value = builder->CreateXor(a, b);
2569 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::bitwise_or)) {
2570 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2571 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2572 Value *b = codegen(op->args[1]);
2573 value = builder->CreateOr(a, b);
2574 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::bitwise_not)) {
2575 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 1);
2576 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2577 value = builder->CreateNot(a);
2578 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::reinterpret)) {
2579 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 1);
2580 Type dst = op->type;
2581 Type src = op->args[0].type();
2582 llvm::Type *llvm_dst = llvm_type_of(dst);
2583 value = codegen(op->args[0]);
2584 if (src.is_handle() && !dst.is_handle()) {
2585 internal_assert(dst.is_uint() && dst.bits() == 64);
2586
2587 // Handle -> UInt64
2588 llvm::DataLayout d(module.get());
2589 if (d.getPointerSize() == 4) {
2590 llvm::Type *intermediate = llvm_type_of(UInt(32, dst.lanes()));
2591 value = builder->CreatePtrToInt(value, intermediate);
2592 value = builder->CreateZExt(value, llvm_dst);
2593 } else if (d.getPointerSize() == 8) {
2594 value = builder->CreatePtrToInt(value, llvm_dst);
2595 } else {
2596 internal_error << "Pointer size is neither 4 nor 8 bytes\n";
2597 }
2598
2599 } else if (dst.is_handle() && !src.is_handle()) {
2600 internal_assert(src.is_uint() && src.bits() == 64);
2601
2602 // UInt64 -> Handle
2603 llvm::DataLayout d(module.get());
2604 if (d.getPointerSize() == 4) {
2605 llvm::Type *intermediate = llvm_type_of(UInt(32, src.lanes()));
2606 value = builder->CreateTrunc(value, intermediate);
2607 value = builder->CreateIntToPtr(value, llvm_dst);
2608 } else if (d.getPointerSize() == 8) {
2609 value = builder->CreateIntToPtr(value, llvm_dst);
2610 } else {
2611 internal_error << "Pointer size is neither 4 nor 8 bytes\n";
2612 }
2613
2614 } else {
2615 if (src.is_scalar() && dst.is_vector()) {
2616 // If the source type is a scalar, we promote it to an
2617 // equivalent vector of width one before doing the
2618 // bitcast, because llvm's bitcast operator doesn't
2619 // want to convert between scalars and vectors.
2620 value = create_broadcast(value, 1);
2621 }
2622 if (src.is_vector() && dst.is_scalar()) {
2623 // Similarly, if we're converting from a vector to a
2624 // scalar, convert to a vector of width 1 first, and
2625 // then extract the first lane.
2626 llvm_dst = get_vector_type(llvm_dst, 1);
2627 }
2628 value = builder->CreateBitCast(value, llvm_dst);
2629 if (src.is_vector() && dst.is_scalar()) {
2630 value = builder->CreateExtractElement(value, (uint64_t)0);
2631 }
2632 }
2633 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::shift_left)) {
2634 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2635 if (op->args[1].type().is_uint()) {
2636 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2637 Value *b = codegen(op->args[1]);
2638 value = builder->CreateShl(a, b);
2639 } else {
2640 value = codegen(lower_signed_shift_left(op->args[0], op->args[1]));
2641 }
2642 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::shift_right)) {
2643 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2644 if (op->args[1].type().is_uint()) {
2645 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2646 Value *b = codegen(op->args[1]);
2647 if (op->type.is_int()) {
2648 value = builder->CreateAShr(a, b);
2649 } else {
2650 value = builder->CreateLShr(a, b);
2651 }
2652 } else {
2653 value = codegen(lower_signed_shift_right(op->args[0], op->args[1]));
2654 }
2655 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::abs)) {
2656 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 1);
2657 // Generate select(x >= 0, x, -x) instead
2658 string x_name = unique_name('x');
2659 Expr x = Variable::make(op->args[0].type(), x_name);
2660 value = codegen(Let::make(x_name, op->args[0], select(x >= 0, x, -x)));
2661 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::absd)) {
2662 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2663 Expr a = op->args[0];
2664 Expr b = op->args[1];
2665 string a_name = unique_name('a');
2666 string b_name = unique_name('b');
2667 Expr a_var = Variable::make(op->args[0].type(), a_name);
2668 Expr b_var = Variable::make(op->args[1].type(), b_name);
2669 codegen(Let::make(a_name, op->args[0],
2670 Let::make(b_name, op->args[1],
2671 Select::make(a_var < b_var, b_var - a_var, a_var - b_var))));
2672 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::div_round_to_zero)) {
2673 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2674 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2675 Value *b = codegen(op->args[1]);
2676 if (op->type.is_int()) {
2677 value = builder->CreateSDiv(a, b);
2678 } else if (op->type.is_uint()) {
2679 value = builder->CreateUDiv(a, b);
2680 } else {
2681 internal_error << "div_round_to_zero of non-integer type.\n";
2682 }
2683 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::mod_round_to_zero)) {
2684 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2685 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2686 Value *b = codegen(op->args[1]);
2687 if (op->type.is_int()) {
2688 value = builder->CreateSRem(a, b);
2689 } else if (op->type.is_uint()) {
2690 value = builder->CreateURem(a, b);
2691 } else {
2692 internal_error << "mod_round_to_zero of non-integer type.\n";
2693 }
2694 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::lerp)) {
2695 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 3);
2696 // If we need to upgrade the type, do the entire lerp in the
2697 // upgraded type for better precision.
2698 // TODO: This might be surprising behavior?
2699 Type t = upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(op->type);
2700 Type wt = upgrade_type_for_arithmetic(op->args[2].type());
2701 Expr e = lower_lerp(cast(t, op->args[0]),
2702 cast(t, op->args[1]),
2703 cast(wt, op->args[2]));
2704 e = cast(op->type, e);
2705 codegen(e);
2706 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::popcount)) {
2707 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 1);
2708 std::vector<llvm::Type *> arg_type(1);
2709 arg_type[0] = llvm_type_of(op->args[0].type());
2710 llvm::Function *fn = llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module.get(), llvm::Intrinsic::ctpop, arg_type);
2711 Value *a = codegen(op->args[0]);
2712 CallInst *call = builder->CreateCall(fn, a);
2713 value = call;
2714 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::count_leading_zeros) ||
2715 op->is_intrinsic(Call::count_trailing_zeros)) {
2716 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 1);
2717 std::vector<llvm::Type *> arg_type(1);
2718 arg_type[0] = llvm_type_of(op->args[0].type());
2719 llvm::Function *fn = llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(module.get(),
2720 (op->is_intrinsic(Call::count_leading_zeros)) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ctlz : llvm::Intrinsic::cttz,
2721 arg_type);
2722 llvm::Value *is_const_zero_undef = llvm::ConstantInt::getFalse(*context);
2723 llvm::Value *args[2] = {codegen(op->args[0]), is_const_zero_undef};
2724 CallInst *call = builder->CreateCall(fn, args);
2725 value = call;
2726 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::return_second)) {
2727 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2728 codegen(op->args[0]);
2729 value = codegen(op->args[1]);
2730 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::if_then_else)) {
2731 Expr cond = op->args[0];
2732 if (const Broadcast *b = cond.as<Broadcast>()) {
2733 cond = b->value;
2734 }
2735 if (cond.type().is_vector()) {
2736 scalarize(op);
2737 } else {
2738
2739 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 3);
2740
2741 BasicBlock *true_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "true_bb", function);
2742 BasicBlock *false_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "false_bb", function);
2743 BasicBlock *after_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "after_bb", function);
2744 Value *c = codegen(cond);
2745 if (c->getType() != i1_t) {
2746 c = builder->CreateIsNotNull(c);
2747 }
2748 builder->CreateCondBr(c, true_bb, false_bb);
2749 builder->SetInsertPoint(true_bb);
2750 Value *true_value = codegen(op->args[1]);
2751 builder->CreateBr(after_bb);
2752 BasicBlock *true_pred = builder->GetInsertBlock();
2753
2754 builder->SetInsertPoint(false_bb);
2755 Value *false_value = codegen(op->args[2]);
2756 builder->CreateBr(after_bb);
2757 BasicBlock *false_pred = builder->GetInsertBlock();
2758
2759 builder->SetInsertPoint(after_bb);
2760 PHINode *phi = builder->CreatePHI(true_value->getType(), 2);
2761 phi->addIncoming(true_value, true_pred);
2762 phi->addIncoming(false_value, false_pred);
2763
2764 value = phi;
2765 }
2766 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::require)) {
2767 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 3);
2768 Expr cond = op->args[0];
2769 if (cond.type().is_vector()) {
2770 scalarize(op);
2771 } else {
2772 Value *c = codegen(cond);
2773 create_assertion(c, op->args[2]);
2774 value = codegen(op->args[1]);
2775 }
2776 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::make_struct)) {
2777 if (op->type.is_vector()) {
2778 // Make a vector of pointers to distinct structs
2779 scalarize(op);
2780 } else if (op->args.empty()) {
2781 // Empty structs can be emitted for arrays of size zero
2782 // (e.g. the shape of a zero-dimensional buffer). We
2783 // generate a null in this situation. */
2784 value = ConstantPointerNull::get(dyn_cast<PointerType>(llvm_type_of(op->type)));
2785 } else {
2786 // Codegen each element.
2787 bool all_same_type = true;
2788 vector<llvm::Value *> args(op->args.size());
2789 vector<llvm::Type *> types(op->args.size());
2790 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i++) {
2791 args[i] = codegen(op->args[i]);
2792 types[i] = args[i]->getType();
2793 all_same_type &= (types[0] == types[i]);
2794 }
2795
2796 // Use either a single scalar, a fixed-size array, or a
2797 // struct. The struct type would always be correct, but
2798 // the array or scalar type produce slightly simpler IR.
2799 if (args.size() == 1) {
2800 value = create_alloca_at_entry(types[0], 1);
2801 builder->CreateStore(args[0], value);
2802 } else {
2803 llvm::Type *aggregate_t = (all_same_type ? (llvm::Type *)ArrayType::get(types[0], types.size()) : (llvm::Type *)StructType::get(*context, types));
2804
2805 value = create_alloca_at_entry(aggregate_t, 1);
2806 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.size(); i++) {
2807 Value *elem_ptr = builder->CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_32(aggregate_t, value, 0, i);
2808 builder->CreateStore(args[i], elem_ptr);
2809 }
2810 }
2811 }
2812 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::saturating_add) || op->is_intrinsic(Call::saturating_sub)) {
2813 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 2);
2814
2815 // Try to fold the vector reduce for a call to saturating_add
2816 const bool folded = try_to_fold_vector_reduce<Call>(op->args[0], op->args[1]);
2817
2818 if (!folded) {
2819 std::string intrin;
2820 if (op->type.is_int()) {
2821 intrin = "llvm.s";
2822 } else {
2823 internal_assert(op->type.is_uint());
2824 intrin = "llvm.u";
2825 }
2826 if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::saturating_add)) {
2827 intrin += "add.sat.";
2828 } else {
2829 internal_assert(op->is_intrinsic(Call::saturating_sub));
2830 intrin += "sub.sat.";
2831 }
2832 if (op->type.lanes() > 1) {
2833 intrin += "v" + std::to_string(op->type.lanes());
2834 }
2835 intrin += "i" + std::to_string(op->type.bits());

2837 }
2838 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::stringify)) {
2839 internal_assert(!op->args.empty());
2840
2841 if (op->type.is_vector()) {
2842 scalarize(op);
2843 } else {
2844
2845 // Compute the maximum possible size of the message.
2846 int buf_size = 1; // One for the terminating zero.
2847 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i++) {
2848 Type t = op->args[i].type();
2849 if (op->args[i].as<StringImm>()) {
2850 buf_size += op->args[i].as<StringImm>()->value.size();
2851 } else if (t.is_int() || t.is_uint()) {
2852 buf_size += 19; // 2^64 = 18446744073709551616
2853 } else if (t.is_float()) {
2854 if (t.bits() == 32) {
2855 buf_size += 47; // %f format of max negative float
2856 } else {
2857 buf_size += 14; // Scientific notation with 6 decimal places.
2858 }
2859 } else if (t == type_of<halide_buffer_t *>()) {
2860 // Not a strict upper bound (there isn't one), but ought to be enough for most buffers.
2861 buf_size += 512;
2862 } else {
2863 internal_assert(t.is_handle());
2864 buf_size += 18; // 0x0123456789abcdef
2865 }
2866 }
2867 // Round up to a multiple of 16 bytes.
2868 buf_size = ((buf_size + 15) / 16) * 16;
2869
2870 // Clamp to at most 8k.
2871 buf_size = std::min(8 * 1024, buf_size);
2872
2873 // Allocate a stack array to hold the message.
2874 llvm::Value *buf = create_alloca_at_entry(i8_t, buf_size);

2879 llvm::Function *append_string = module->getFunction("halide_string_to_string");
2880 llvm::Function *append_int64 = module->getFunction("halide_int64_to_string");
2881 llvm::Function *append_uint64 = module->getFunction("halide_uint64_to_string");
2882 llvm::Function *append_double = module->getFunction("halide_double_to_string");
2883 llvm::Function *append_pointer = module->getFunction("halide_pointer_to_string");
2884 llvm::Function *append_buffer = module->getFunction("halide_buffer_to_string");
2885
2886 internal_assert(append_string);
2887 internal_assert(append_int64);
2888 internal_assert(append_uint64);
2889 internal_assert(append_double);
2890 internal_assert(append_pointer);
2891 internal_assert(append_buffer);
2892
2893 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i++) {
2894 const StringImm *s = op->args[i].as<StringImm>();
2895 Type t = op->args[i].type();
2896 internal_assert(t.lanes() == 1);
2897 vector<Value *> call_args(2);
2898 call_args[0] = dst;
2899 call_args[1] = buf_end;

2902 call_args.push_back(codegen(op->args[i]));
2903 dst = builder->CreateCall(append_string, call_args);
2904 } else if (t.is_bool()) {
2905 Value *a = codegen(op->args[i]);

2908 call_args.push_back(builder->CreateSelect(a, t, f));
2909 dst = builder->CreateCall(append_string, call_args);
2910 } else if (t.is_int()) {
2911 call_args.push_back(codegen(Cast::make(Int(64), op->args[i])));
2912 call_args.push_back(ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 1));
2913 dst = builder->CreateCall(append_int64, call_args);
2914 } else if (t.is_uint()) {
2915 call_args.push_back(codegen(Cast::make(UInt(64), op->args[i])));
2916 call_args.push_back(ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 1));
2917 dst = builder->CreateCall(append_uint64, call_args);
2918 } else if (t.is_float()) {
2919 call_args.push_back(codegen(Cast::make(Float(64), op->args[i])));
2920 // Use scientific notation for doubles
2921 call_args.push_back(ConstantInt::get(i32_t, t.bits() == 64 ? 1 : 0));
2922 dst = builder->CreateCall(append_double, call_args);
2923 } else if (t == type_of<halide_buffer_t *>()) {
2924 Value *buf = codegen(op->args[i]);
2925 buf = builder->CreatePointerCast(buf, append_buffer->getFunctionType()->getParamType(2));
2926 call_args.push_back(buf);
2927 dst = builder->CreateCall(append_buffer, call_args);
2928 } else {
2929 internal_assert(t.is_handle());
2930 call_args.push_back(codegen(op->args[i]));
2931 dst = builder->CreateCall(append_pointer, call_args);
2932 }

2934 if (get_target().has_feature(Target::MSAN)) {

2936 // it would be more accurate to just mark (dst - buf)

2938 vector<Value *> annotate_args(3);
2939 annotate_args[0] = get_user_context();

2941 annotate_args[2] = codegen(Cast::make(Int(64), buf_size));
2942 builder->CreateCall(annotate, annotate_args);
2943 }
2944 value = buf;
2945 }
2946 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::memoize_expr)) {

2948 // codegen. Ignore arguments beyond the first as they are only
2949 // used in the cache key.
2950 internal_assert(!op->args.empty());
2951 value = codegen(op->args[0]);
2952 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::alloca)) {

2954 // const, or a call to size_of_halide_buffer_t.
2955 internal_assert(op->args.size() == 1);

2981 FunctionType *func_t = FunctionType::get(void_t, arg_types, false);

2984 }

2987 value = register_destructor(f, arg, Always);
2988 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::call_cached_indirect_function)) {
2989 // Arguments to call_cached_indirect_function are of the form
2990 //
2991 // cond_1, "sub_function_name_1",
2992 // cond_2, "sub_function_name_2",
2993 // ...
2994 // cond_N, "sub_function_name_N"
2995 //
2996 // This will generate code that corresponds (roughly) to
2997 //
2998 // static FunctionPtr f = []{
2999 // if (cond_1) return sub_function_name_1;
3000 // if (cond_2) return sub_function_name_2;
3001 // ...
3002 // if (cond_N) return sub_function_name_N;
3003 // }
3004 // return f(args)
3005 //
3006 // i.e.: the conditions will be evaluated *in order*; the first one
3007 // evaluating to true will have its corresponding function cached,
3008 // which will be used to complete this (and all subsequent) calls.
3009 //
3010 // The final condition (cond_N) must evaluate to a constant TRUE
3011 // value (so that the final function will be selected if all others
3012 // fail); failure to do so will cause unpredictable results.
3013 //
3014 // There is currently no way to clear the cached function pointer.
3015 //
3016 // It is assumed/required that all of the conditions are "pure"; each
3017 // must evaluate to the same value (within a given runtime environment)
3018 // across multiple evaluations.
3019 //
3020 // It is assumed/required that all of the sub-functions have arguments
3021 // (and return values) that are identical to those of this->function.
3022 //
3023 // Note that we require >= 4 arguments: fewer would imply
3024 // only one condition+function pair, which is pointless to use
3025 // (the function should always be called directly).
3026 //
3027 internal_assert(op->args.size() >= 4);
3028 internal_assert(!(op->args.size() & 1));
3029
3030 // Gather information we need about each function.
3031 struct SubFn {
3032 llvm::Function *fn;
3033 llvm::GlobalValue *fn_ptr;
3034 Expr cond;
3035 };
3036 vector<SubFn> sub_fns;
3037 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i += 2) {
3038 const string sub_fn_name = op->args[i + 1].as<StringImm>()->value;
3039 string extern_sub_fn_name = sub_fn_name;
3040 llvm::Function *sub_fn = module->getFunction(sub_fn_name);
3041 if (!sub_fn) {
3042 extern_sub_fn_name = get_mangled_names(sub_fn_name,
3043 LinkageType::External,
3044 NameMangling::Default,
3045 current_function_args,
3046 get_target())
3047 .extern_name;
3048 debug(1) << "Did not find function " << sub_fn_name
3049 << ", assuming extern \"C\" " << extern_sub_fn_name << "\n";
3050 vector<llvm::Type *> arg_types;
3051 for (const auto &arg : function->args()) {
3052 arg_types.push_back(arg.getType());
3053 }
3054 llvm::Type *result_type = llvm_type_of(upgrade_type_for_argument_passing(op->type));
3055 FunctionType *func_t = FunctionType::get(result_type, arg_types, false);
3056 sub_fn = llvm::Function::Create(func_t, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
3057 extern_sub_fn_name, module.get());
3058 sub_fn->setCallingConv(CallingConv::C);
3059 }
3060
3061 llvm::GlobalValue *sub_fn_ptr = module->getNamedValue(extern_sub_fn_name);
3062 if (!sub_fn_ptr) {
3063 debug(1) << "Did not find function ptr " << extern_sub_fn_name << ", assuming extern \"C\".\n";
3064 sub_fn_ptr = new GlobalVariable(*module, sub_fn->getType(),
3065 /*isConstant*/ true, GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
3066 /*initializer*/ nullptr, extern_sub_fn_name);
3067 }
3068 auto cond = op->args[i];
3069 sub_fns.push_back({sub_fn, sub_fn_ptr, cond});
3070 }
3071
3072 // Create a null-initialized global to track this object.
3073 auto *const base_fn = sub_fns.back().fn;
3074 const string global_name = unique_name(base_fn->getName().str() + "_indirect_fn_ptr");
3075 GlobalVariable *global = new GlobalVariable(
3076 *module,
3077 base_fn->getType(),
3078 /*isConstant*/ false,
3079 GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
3080 ConstantPointerNull::get(base_fn->getType()),
3081 global_name);
3082 LoadInst *loaded_value = builder->CreateLoad(global->getType()->getPointerElementType(), global);
3083
3084 BasicBlock *global_inited_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "global_inited_bb", function);
3085 BasicBlock *global_not_inited_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "global_not_inited_bb", function);
3086 BasicBlock *call_fn_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "call_fn_bb", function);
3087
3088 // Only init the global if not already inited.
3089 //
3090 // Note that we deliberately do not attempt to make this threadsafe via (e.g.) mutexes;
3091 // the requirements of the conditions above mean that multiple writes *should* only
3092 // be able to re-write the same value, which is harmless for our purposes, and
3093 // avoiding such code simplifies and speeds the resulting code.
3094 //
3095 // (Note that if we ever need to add a way to clear the cached function pointer,
3096 // we may need to reconsider this, to avoid amusingly horrible race conditions.)
3097 builder->CreateCondBr(builder->CreateIsNotNull(loaded_value),
3098 global_inited_bb, global_not_inited_bb, very_likely_branch);
3099

3101 builder->SetInsertPoint(global_not_inited_bb);

3103 for (int i = sub_fns.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
3104 const auto sub_fn = sub_fns[i];
3105 if (!selected_value) {
3106 selected_value = sub_fn.fn_ptr;
3107 } else {
3108 Value *c = codegen(sub_fn.cond);
3109 selected_value = builder->CreateSelect(c, sub_fn.fn_ptr, selected_value);
3110 }
3111 }
3112 builder->CreateStore(selected_value, global);
3113 builder->CreateBr(call_fn_bb);
3114
3115 // Just an incoming edge for the Phi node
3116 builder->SetInsertPoint(global_inited_bb);
3117 builder->CreateBr(call_fn_bb);
3118
3119 builder->SetInsertPoint(call_fn_bb);
3120 PHINode *phi = builder->CreatePHI(selected_value->getType(), 2);
3121 phi->addIncoming(selected_value, global_not_inited_bb);
3122 phi->addIncoming(loaded_value, global_inited_bb);
3123

3125 for (auto &arg : function->args()) {
3126 call_args.push_back(&arg);
3127 }
3128
3129 llvm::CallInst *call = builder->CreateCall(base_fn->getFunctionType(), phi, call_args);
3130 value = call;
3131 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::prefetch)) {
3132 user_assert((op->args.size() == 4) && is_const_one(op->args[2]))

3141 // need to cast the argument, which might be a pointer to a

3147
3148 } else if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::signed_integer_overflow)) {

3172 }
3173 value = codegen(lowered);

3249 internal_assert(e.type().is_float());

3270 // Codegen the args
3271 vector<Value *> args(op->args.size());
3272 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i++) {
3273 args[i] = codegen(op->args[i]);
3274 }
3275
3276 llvm::Function *fn = module->getFunction(name);
3277
3278 llvm::Type *result_type = llvm_type_of(upgrade_type_for_argument_passing(op->type));
3279
3280 // Add a user context arg as needed. It's never a vector.
3281 bool takes_user_context = function_takes_user_context(op->name);
3282 if (takes_user_context) {
3283 internal_assert(fn) << "External function " << op->name << " is marked as taking user_context, but is not in the runtime module. Check if runtime_api.cpp needs to be rebuilt.\n";
3284 debug(4) << "Adding user_context to " << op->name << " args\n";
3285 args.insert(args.begin(), get_user_context());
3286 }
3287
3288 // If we can't find it, declare it extern "C"
3289 if (!fn) {
3290 vector<llvm::Type *> arg_types(args.size());
3291 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.size(); i++) {
3292 arg_types[i] = args[i]->getType();
3293 if (arg_types[i]->isVectorTy()) {
3294 VectorType *vt = dyn_cast<VectorType>(arg_types[i]);
3295 arg_types[i] = vt->getElementType();
3296 }
3297 }
3298
3299 llvm::Type *scalar_result_type = result_type;
3300 if (result_type->isVectorTy()) {
3301 VectorType *vt = dyn_cast<VectorType>(result_type);
3302 scalar_result_type = vt->getElementType();
3303 }
3304
3305 FunctionType *func_t = FunctionType::get(scalar_result_type, arg_types, false);
3306
3307 fn = llvm::Function::Create(func_t, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, name, module.get());
3308 fn->setCallingConv(CallingConv::C);
3309 debug(4) << "Did not find " << op->name << ". Declared it extern \"C\".\n";
3310 } else {
3311 debug(4) << "Found " << op->name << "\n";
3312
3313 // TODO: Say something more accurate here as there is now
3314 // partial information in the handle_type field, but it is
3315 // not clear it can be matched to the LLVM types and it is
3316 // not always there.
3317 // Halide's type system doesn't preserve pointer types
3318 // correctly (they just get called "Handle()"), so we may
3319 // need to pointer cast to the appropriate type. Only look at
3320 // fixed params (not varags) in llvm function.
3321 FunctionType *func_t = fn->getFunctionType();
3322 for (size_t i = takes_user_context ? 1 : 0;
3323 i < std::min(args.size(), (size_t)(func_t->getNumParams()));
3324 i++) {
3325 Expr halide_arg = takes_user_context ? op->args[i - 1] : op->args[i];
3326 if (halide_arg.type().is_handle()) {
3327 llvm::Type *t = func_t->getParamType(i);
3328
3329 // Widen to vector-width as needed. If the
3330 // function doesn't actually take a vector,
3331 // individual lanes will be extracted below.
3332 if (halide_arg.type().is_vector() &&
3333 !t->isVectorTy()) {
3334 t = get_vector_type(t, halide_arg.type().lanes());
3335 }
3336
3337 if (t != args[i]->getType()) {
3338 debug(4) << "Pointer casting argument to extern call: "
3339 << halide_arg << "\n";
3340 args[i] = builder->CreatePointerCast(args[i], t);
3341 }
3342 }
3343 }
3344 }
3345
3346 if (op->type.is_scalar()) {
3347 CallInst *call = builder->CreateCall(fn, args);
3348 if (op->is_pure()) {
3349 call->setDoesNotAccessMemory();
3350 }
3351 call->setDoesNotThrow();
3352 value = call;
3353 } else {
3354
3355 // Check if a vector version of the function already
3356 // exists at some useful width.
3357 pair<llvm::Function *, int> vec =
3358 find_vector_runtime_function(name, op->type.lanes());
3359 llvm::Function *vec_fn = vec.first;
3360 int w = vec.second;
3361
3362 if (vec_fn) {
3363 value = call_intrin(llvm_type_of(op->type), w,
3364 get_llvm_function_name(vec_fn), args);
3365 } else {
3366
3367 // No vector version found. Scalarize. Extract each simd
3368 // lane in turn and do one scalar call to the function.
3369 value = UndefValue::get(result_type);
3370 for (int i = 0; i < op->type.lanes(); i++) {
3371 Value *idx = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i);
3372 vector<Value *> arg_lane(args.size());
3373 for (size_t j = 0; j < args.size(); j++) {
3374 if (args[j]->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
3375 arg_lane[j] = builder->CreateExtractElement(args[j], idx);
3376 } else {
3377 arg_lane[j] = args[j];
3378 }
3379 }
3380 CallInst *call = builder->CreateCall(fn, arg_lane);
3381 if (op->is_pure()) {
3382 call->setDoesNotAccessMemory();
3383 }
3384 call->setDoesNotThrow();
3385 if (!call->getType()->isVoidTy()) {
3386 value = builder->CreateInsertElement(value, call, idx);
3387 } // otherwise leave it as undef.
3388 }
3389 }
3390 }
3391 }
3392}

3414Constant *CodeGen_LLVM::create_string_constant(const string &s) {
3415 map<string, Constant *>::iterator iter = string_constants.find(s);
3416 if (iter == string_constants.end()) {
3417 vector<char> data;
3418 data.reserve(s.size() + 1);
3419 data.insert(data.end(), s.begin(), s.end());
3420 data.push_back(0);
3421 Constant *val = create_binary_blob(data, "str");
3422 string_constants[s] = val;
3423 return val;
3424 } else {
3425 return iter->second;
3426 }

3428
3429Constant *CodeGen_LLVM::create_binary_blob(const vector<char> &data, const string &name, bool constant) {
3430 internal_assert(!data.empty());
3431 llvm::Type *type = ArrayType::get(i8_t, data.size());
3432 GlobalVariable *global = new GlobalVariable(*module, type,
3433 constant, GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
3434 nullptr, name);
3435 ArrayRef<unsigned char> data_array((const unsigned char *)&data[0], data.size());
3436 global->setInitializer(ConstantDataArray::get(*context, data_array));
3437 size_t alignment = 32;
3438 size_t native_vector_bytes = (size_t)(native_vector_bits() / 8);
3439 if (data.size() > alignment && native_vector_bytes > alignment) {
3440 alignment = native_vector_bytes;
3441 }
3442 global->setAlignment(llvm::Align(alignment));
3443
3444 Constant *zero = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0);
3445 Constant *zeros[] = {zero, zero};
3446 Constant *ptr = ConstantExpr::getInBoundsGetElementPtr(type, global, zeros);
3447 return ptr;
3448}
3449
3450void CodeGen_LLVM::create_assertion(Value *cond, const Expr &message, llvm::Value *error_code) {
3451
3452 internal_assert(!message.defined() || message.type() == Int(32))
3453 << "Assertion result is not an int: " << message;
3454
3455 if (target.has_feature(Target::NoAsserts)) {
3456 return;
3457 }
3458
3459 // If the condition is a vector, fold it down to a scalar
3460 VectorType *vt = dyn_cast<VectorType>(cond->getType());
3461 if (vt) {
3462 Value *scalar_cond = builder->CreateExtractElement(cond, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0));
3463 for (int i = 1; i < get_vector_num_elements(vt); i++) {
3464 Value *lane = builder->CreateExtractElement(cond, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i));
3465 scalar_cond = builder->CreateAnd(scalar_cond, lane);
3466 }
3467 cond = scalar_cond;
3468 }
3469
3470 // Make a new basic block for the assert
3471 BasicBlock *assert_fails_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "assert failed", function);
3472 BasicBlock *assert_succeeds_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "assert succeeded", function);
3473
3474 // If the condition fails, enter the assert body, otherwise, enter the block after
3475 builder->CreateCondBr(cond, assert_succeeds_bb, assert_fails_bb, very_likely_branch);
3476
3477 // Build the failure case
3478 builder->SetInsertPoint(assert_fails_bb);
3479
3480 // Call the error handler
3481 if (!error_code) {
3482 error_code = codegen(message);
3483 }
3484
3485 return_with_error_code(error_code);
3486
3487 // Continue on using the success case
3488 builder->SetInsertPoint(assert_succeeds_bb);
3489}
3490
3491void CodeGen_LLVM::return_with_error_code(llvm::Value *error_code) {
3492 // Branch to the destructor block, which cleans up and then bails out.
3493 BasicBlock *dtors = get_destructor_block();
3494
3495 // Hook up our error code to the phi node that the destructor block starts with.
3496 PHINode *phi = dyn_cast<PHINode>(dtors->begin());
3497 internal_assert(phi) << "The destructor block is supposed to start with a phi node\n";
3498 phi->addIncoming(error_code, builder->GetInsertBlock());
3499
3500 builder->CreateBr(get_destructor_block());
3501}

3508 name = std::string("consume ") + op->name;
3509 }

3511 builder->CreateBr(produce);

3514}
3515
3516void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const For *op) {
3517 Value *min = codegen(op->min);
3518 Value *extent = codegen(op->extent);
3519 const Acquire *acquire = op->body.as<Acquire>();
3520
3521 if (op->for_type == ForType::Parallel ||
3522 (op->for_type == ForType::Serial &&
3523 acquire &&
3524 !expr_uses_var(acquire->count, op->name))) {
3525 do_as_parallel_task(op);
3526 } else if (op->for_type == ForType::Serial) {
3527
3528 Value *max = builder->CreateNSWAdd(min, extent);
3529
3530 BasicBlock *preheader_bb = builder->GetInsertBlock();
3531
3532 // Make a new basic block for the loop
3533 BasicBlock *loop_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, std::string("for ") + op->name, function);
3534 // Create the block that comes after the loop
3535 BasicBlock *after_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, std::string("end for ") + op->name, function);
3536
3537 // If min < max, fall through to the loop bb
3538 Value *enter_condition = builder->CreateICmpSLT(min, max);
3539 builder->CreateCondBr(enter_condition, loop_bb, after_bb, very_likely_branch);
3540 builder->SetInsertPoint(loop_bb);
3541
3542 // Make our phi node.
3543 PHINode *phi = builder->CreatePHI(i32_t, 2);
3544 phi->addIncoming(min, preheader_bb);
3545
3546 // Within the loop, the variable is equal to the phi value
3547 sym_push(op->name, phi);
3548
3549 // Emit the loop body
3550 codegen(op->body);
3551
3552 // Update the counter
3553 Value *next_var = builder->CreateNSWAdd(phi, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 1));
3554
3555 // Add the back-edge to the phi node
3556 phi->addIncoming(next_var, builder->GetInsertBlock());
3557
3558 // Maybe exit the loop
3559 Value *end_condition = builder->CreateICmpNE(next_var, max);
3560 builder->CreateCondBr(end_condition, loop_bb, after_bb);
3561
3562 builder->SetInsertPoint(after_bb);
3563
3564 // Pop the loop variable from the scope
3565 sym_pop(op->name);
3566 } else {
3567 internal_error << "Unknown type of For node. Only Serial and Parallel For nodes should survive down to codegen.\n";
3568 }
3569}
3570
3571void CodeGen_LLVM::do_parallel_tasks(const vector<ParallelTask> &tasks) {
3572 Closure closure;
3573 for (const auto &t : tasks) {
3574 Stmt s = t.body;
3575 if (!t.loop_var.empty()) {
3576 s = LetStmt::make(t.loop_var, 0, s);
3577 }
3578 s.accept(&closure);
3579 }
3580
3581 // Allocate a closure
3582 StructType *closure_t = build_closure_type(closure, halide_buffer_t_type, context);
3583 Value *closure_ptr = create_alloca_at_entry(closure_t, 1);
3584
3585 // Fill in the closure
3586 pack_closure(closure_t, closure_ptr, closure, symbol_table, halide_buffer_t_type, builder);
3587
3588 closure_ptr = builder->CreatePointerCast(closure_ptr, i8_t->getPointerTo());
3589
3590 int num_tasks = (int)tasks.size();
3591
3592 // Make space on the stack for the tasks
3593 llvm::Value *task_stack_ptr = create_alloca_at_entry(parallel_task_t_type, num_tasks);
3594
3595 llvm::Type *args_t[] = {i8_t->getPointerTo(), i32_t, i8_t->getPointerTo()};
3596 FunctionType *task_t = FunctionType::get(i32_t, args_t, false);
3597 llvm::Type *loop_args_t[] = {i8_t->getPointerTo(), i32_t, i32_t, i8_t->getPointerTo(), i8_t->getPointerTo()};
3598 FunctionType *loop_task_t = FunctionType::get(i32_t, loop_args_t, false);
3599
3600 Value *result = nullptr;
3601
3602 for (int i = 0; i < num_tasks; i++) {
3603 ParallelTask t = tasks[i];
3604
3605 // Analyze the task body
3606 class MayBlock : public IRVisitor {
3607 using IRVisitor::visit;
3608 void visit(const Acquire *op) override {
3609 result = true;
3610 }
3611
3612 public:
3613 bool result = false;
3614 };
3615
3616 // TODO(zvookin|abadams): This makes multiple passes over the
3617 // IR to cover each node. (One tree walk produces the min
3618 // thread count for all nodes, but we redo each subtree when
3619 // compiling a given node.) Ideally we'd move to a lowering pass
3620 // that converts our parallelism constructs to Call nodes, or
3621 // direct hardware operations in some cases.
3622 // Also, this code has to exactly mirror the logic in get_parallel_tasks.
3623 // It would be better to do one pass on the tree and centralize the task
3624 // deduction logic in one place.
3625 class MinThreads : public IRVisitor {
3626 using IRVisitor::visit;
3627
3628 std::pair<Stmt, int> skip_acquires(Stmt first) {
3629 int count = 0;
3630 while (first.defined()) {
3631 const Acquire *acq = first.as<Acquire>();
3632 if (acq == nullptr) {
3633 break;
3634 }
3635 count++;
3636 first = acq->body;
3637 }
3638 return {first, count};
3639 }
3640
3641 void visit(const Fork *op) override {
3642 int total_threads = 0;
3643 int direct_acquires = 0;
3644 // Take the sum of min threads across all
3645 // cascaded Fork nodes.
3646 const Fork *node = op;
3647 while (node != nullptr) {
3648 result = 0;
3649 auto after_acquires = skip_acquires(node->first);
3650 direct_acquires += after_acquires.second;
3651
3652 after_acquires.first.accept(this);
3653 total_threads += result;
3654
3655 const Fork *continued_branches = node->rest.as<Fork>();
3656 if (continued_branches == nullptr) {
3657 result = 0;
3658 after_acquires = skip_acquires(node->rest);
3659 direct_acquires += after_acquires.second;
3660 after_acquires.first.accept(this);
3661 total_threads += result;
3662 }
3663 node = continued_branches;
3664 }
3665 if (direct_acquires == 0 && total_threads == 0) {
3666 result = 0;
3667 } else {
3668 result = total_threads + 1;
3669 }
3670 }
3671
3672 void visit(const For *op) override {
3673 result = 0;
3674
3675 if (op->for_type == ForType::Parallel) {
3676 IRVisitor::visit(op);
3677 if (result > 0) {
3678 result += 1;
3679 }
3680 } else if (op->for_type == ForType::Serial) {
3681 auto after_acquires = skip_acquires(op->body);
3682 if (after_acquires.second > 0 &&
3683 !expr_uses_var(op->body.as<Acquire>()->count, op->name)) {
3684 after_acquires.first.accept(this);
3685 result++;
3686 } else {
3687 IRVisitor::visit(op);
3688 }
3689 } else {
3690 IRVisitor::visit(op);
3691 }
3692 }
3693
3694 // This is a "standalone" Acquire and will result in its own task.
3695 // Treat it requiring one more thread than its body.
3696 void visit(const Acquire *op) override {
3697 result = 0;
3698 auto after_inner_acquires = skip_acquires(op);
3699 after_inner_acquires.first.accept(this);
3700 result = result + 1;
3701 }
3702
3703 void visit(const Block *op) override {
3704 result = 0;
3705 op->first.accept(this);
3706 int result_first = result;
3707 result = 0;
3708 op->rest.accept(this);
3709 result = std::max(result, result_first);
3710 }
3711
3712 public:
3713 int result = 0;
3714 };
3715 MinThreads min_threads;
3716 t.body.accept(&min_threads);
3717
3718 // Decide if we're going to call do_par_for or
3719 // do_parallel_tasks. halide_do_par_for is simpler, but
3720 // assumes a bunch of things. Programs that don't use async
3721 // can also enter the task system via do_par_for.
3722 Value *task_parent = sym_get("__task_parent", false);
3723 bool use_do_par_for = (num_tasks == 1 &&
3724 min_threads.result == 0 &&
3725 t.semaphores.empty() &&
3726 !task_parent);
3727
3728 // Make the array of semaphore acquisitions this task needs to do before it runs.
3729 Value *semaphores;
3730 Value *num_semaphores = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, (int)t.semaphores.size());
3731 if (!t.semaphores.empty()) {
3732 semaphores = create_alloca_at_entry(semaphore_acquire_t_type, (int)t.semaphores.size());
3733 for (int i = 0; i < (int)t.semaphores.size(); i++) {
3734 Value *semaphore = codegen(t.semaphores[i].semaphore);
3735 semaphore = builder->CreatePointerCast(semaphore, semaphore_t_type->getPointerTo());
3736 Value *count = codegen(t.semaphores[i].count);
3737 Value *slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(semaphore_acquire_t_type, semaphores, i, 0);
3738 builder->CreateStore(semaphore, slot_ptr);
3739 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(semaphore_acquire_t_type, semaphores, i, 1);
3740 builder->CreateStore(count, slot_ptr);
3741 }
3742 } else {
3743 semaphores = ConstantPointerNull::get(semaphore_acquire_t_type->getPointerTo());
3744 }
3745
3746 FunctionType *fn_type = use_do_par_for ? task_t : loop_task_t;
3747 int closure_arg_idx = use_do_par_for ? 2 : 3;
3748
3749 // Make a new function that does the body
3750 llvm::Function *containing_function = function;
3751 function = llvm::Function::Create(fn_type, llvm::Function::InternalLinkage,
3752 t.name, module.get());
3753
3754 llvm::Value *task_ptr = builder->CreatePointerCast(function, fn_type->getPointerTo());
3755
3756 function->addParamAttr(closure_arg_idx, Attribute::NoAlias);
3757
3758 set_function_attributes_for_target(function, target);
3759
3760 // Make the initial basic block and jump the builder into the new function
3761 IRBuilderBase::InsertPoint call_site = builder->saveIP();
3762 BasicBlock *block = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "entry", function);
3763 builder->SetInsertPoint(block);
3764
3765 // Save the destructor block
3766 BasicBlock *parent_destructor_block = destructor_block;
3767 destructor_block = nullptr;
3768
3769 // Make a new scope to use
3770 Scope<Value *> saved_symbol_table;
3771 symbol_table.swap(saved_symbol_table);
3772
3773 // Get the function arguments
3774
3775 // The user context is first argument of the function; it's
3776 // important that we override the name to be "__user_context",
3777 // since the LLVM function has a random auto-generated name for
3778 // this argument.
3779 llvm::Function::arg_iterator iter = function->arg_begin();
3780 sym_push("__user_context", iterator_to_pointer(iter));
3781
3782 if (use_do_par_for) {
3783 // Next is the loop variable.
3784 ++iter;
3785 sym_push(t.loop_var, iterator_to_pointer(iter));
3786 } else if (!t.loop_var.empty()) {
3787 // We peeled off a loop. Wrap a new loop around the body
3788 // that just does the slice given by the arguments.
3789 string loop_min_name = unique_name('t');
3790 string loop_extent_name = unique_name('t');
3791 t.body = For::make(t.loop_var,
3792 Variable::make(Int(32), loop_min_name),
3793 Variable::make(Int(32), loop_extent_name),
3794 ForType::Serial,
3795 DeviceAPI::None,
3796 t.body);
3797 ++iter;
3798 sym_push(loop_min_name, iterator_to_pointer(iter));
3799 ++iter;
3800 sym_push(loop_extent_name, iterator_to_pointer(iter));
3801 } else {
3802 // This task is not any kind of loop, so skip these args.
3803 ++iter;
3804 ++iter;
3805 }
3806
3807 // The closure pointer is either the last (for halide_do_par_for) or
3808 // second to last argument (for halide_do_parallel_tasks).
3809 ++iter;
3810 iter->setName("closure");
3811 Value *closure_handle = builder->CreatePointerCast(iterator_to_pointer(iter),
3812 closure_t->getPointerTo());
3813
3814 // Load everything from the closure into the new scope
3815 unpack_closure(closure, symbol_table, closure_t, closure_handle, builder);
3816
3817 if (!use_do_par_for) {
3818 // For halide_do_parallel_tasks the threading runtime task parent
3819 // is the last argument.
3820 ++iter;
3821 iter->setName("task_parent");
3822 sym_push("__task_parent", iterator_to_pointer(iter));
3823 }
3824
3825 // Generate the new function body
3826 codegen(t.body);
3827
3828 // Return success
3829 return_with_error_code(ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0));
3830
3831 // Move the builder back to the main function.
3832 builder->restoreIP(call_site);
3833
3834 // Now restore the scope
3835 symbol_table.swap(saved_symbol_table);
3836 function = containing_function;
3837
3838 // Restore the destructor block
3839 destructor_block = parent_destructor_block;
3840
3841 Value *min = codegen(t.min);
3842 Value *extent = codegen(t.extent);
3843 Value *serial = codegen(cast(UInt(8), t.serial));
3844
3845 if (use_do_par_for) {
3846 llvm::Function *do_par_for = module->getFunction("halide_do_par_for");
3847 internal_assert(do_par_for) << "Could not find halide_do_par_for in initial module\n";
3848 do_par_for->addParamAttr(4, Attribute::NoAlias);
3849 Value *args[] = {get_user_context(), task_ptr, min, extent, closure_ptr};
3850 debug(4) << "Creating call to do_par_for\n";
3851 result = builder->CreateCall(do_par_for, args);
3852 } else {
3853 // Populate the task struct
3854 Value *slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 0);
3855 builder->CreateStore(task_ptr, slot_ptr);
3856 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 1);
3857 builder->CreateStore(closure_ptr, slot_ptr);
3858 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 2);
3859 builder->CreateStore(create_string_constant(t.name), slot_ptr);
3860 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 3);
3861 builder->CreateStore(semaphores, slot_ptr);
3862 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 4);
3863 builder->CreateStore(num_semaphores, slot_ptr);
3864 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 5);
3865 builder->CreateStore(min, slot_ptr);
3866 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 6);
3867 builder->CreateStore(extent, slot_ptr);
3868 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 7);
3869 builder->CreateStore(ConstantInt::get(i32_t, min_threads.result), slot_ptr);
3870 slot_ptr = builder->CreateConstGEP2_32(parallel_task_t_type, task_stack_ptr, i, 8);
3871 builder->CreateStore(serial, slot_ptr);
3872 }
3873 }
3874
3875 if (!result) {
3876 llvm::Function *do_parallel_tasks = module->getFunction("halide_do_parallel_tasks");
3877 internal_assert(do_parallel_tasks) << "Could not find halide_do_parallel_tasks in initial module\n";
3878 do_parallel_tasks->addParamAttr(2, Attribute::NoAlias);
3879 Value *task_parent = sym_get("__task_parent", false);
3880 if (!task_parent) {
3881 task_parent = ConstantPointerNull::get(i8_t->getPointerTo()); // void*
3882 }
3883 Value *args[] = {get_user_context(),
3884 ConstantInt::get(i32_t, num_tasks),
3885 task_stack_ptr,
3886 task_parent};
3887 result = builder->CreateCall(do_parallel_tasks, args);
3888 }
3889
3890 // Check for success
3891 Value *did_succeed = builder->CreateICmpEQ(result, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0));
3892 create_assertion(did_succeed, Expr(), result);
3893}

3922void CodeGen_LLVM::get_parallel_tasks(const Stmt &s, vector<ParallelTask> &result, std::pair<string, int> prefix) {
3923 const For *loop = s.as<For>();
3924 const Acquire *acquire = loop ? loop->body.as<Acquire>() : s.as<Acquire>();
3925 if (const Fork *f = s.as<Fork>()) {
3926 add_fork(prefix);
3927 get_parallel_tasks(f->first, result, prefix);
3928 get_parallel_tasks(f->rest, result, prefix);
3929 } else if (!loop && acquire) {
3930 const Variable *v = acquire->semaphore.as<Variable>();
3931 internal_assert(v);
3932 add_suffix(prefix, "." + v->name);
3933 ParallelTask t{s, {}, "", 0, 1, const_false(), task_debug_name(prefix)};
3934 while (acquire) {
3935 t.semaphores.push_back({acquire->semaphore, acquire->count});
3936 t.body = acquire->body;
3937 acquire = t.body.as<Acquire>();
3938 }
3939 result.push_back(t);
3940 } else if (loop && loop->for_type == ForType::Parallel) {
3941 add_suffix(prefix, ".par_for." + loop->name);
3942 result.push_back(ParallelTask{loop->body, {}, loop->name, loop->min, loop->extent, const_false(), task_debug_name(prefix)});
3943 } else if (loop &&
3944 loop->for_type == ForType::Serial &&
3945 acquire &&
3946 !expr_uses_var(acquire->count, loop->name)) {
3947 const Variable *v = acquire->semaphore.as<Variable>();
3948 internal_assert(v);
3949 add_suffix(prefix, ".for." + v->name);
3950 ParallelTask t{loop->body, {}, loop->name, loop->min, loop->extent, const_true(), task_debug_name(prefix)};
3951 while (acquire) {
3952 t.semaphores.push_back({acquire->semaphore, acquire->count});
3953 t.body = acquire->body;
3954 acquire = t.body.as<Acquire>();
3955 }
3956 result.push_back(t);
3957 } else {
3958 add_suffix(prefix, "." + std::to_string(result.size()));
3959 result.push_back(ParallelTask{s, {}, "", 0, 1, const_false(), task_debug_name(prefix)});
3960 }
3961}

3963void CodeGen_LLVM::do_as_parallel_task(const Stmt &s) {
3964 vector<ParallelTask> tasks;
3965 get_parallel_tasks(s, tasks, {function->getName().str(), 0});
3966 do_parallel_tasks(tasks);
3967}

3977void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Store *op) {
3978 if (!emit_atomic_stores) {
3979 // Peel lets off the index to make us more likely to pattern
3980 // match a ramp.
3981 if (const Let *let = op->index.as<Let>()) {
3982 Stmt s = Store::make(op->name, op->value, let->body, op->param, op->predicate, op->alignment);
3983 codegen(LetStmt::make(let->name, let->value, s));
3984 return;
3985 }
3986 }
3987
3988 // Fix up the type
3989 Halide::Type value_type = op->value.type();
3990 Halide::Type storage_type = upgrade_type_for_storage(value_type);
3991 if (value_type != storage_type) {
3992 Expr v = reinterpret(storage_type, op->value);
3993 codegen(Store::make(op->name, v, op->index, op->param, op->predicate, op->alignment));
3994 return;
3995 }
3996
3997 if (inside_atomic_mutex_node) {
3998 user_assert(value_type.is_scalar())
3999 << "The vectorized atomic operation for the store " << op->name
4000 << " is lowered into a mutex lock, which does not support vectorization.\n";
4001 }
4002
4003 bool recursive = (expr_uses_var(op->index, op->name) ||
4004 expr_uses_var(op->value, op->name));
4005 // Issue atomic store if we are inside an atomic node.
4006 if (emit_atomic_stores && recursive) {
4007 codegen_atomic_rmw(op);
4008 return;
4009 }
4010
4011 // Predicated store.
4012 if (!is_const_one(op->predicate)) {
4013 codegen_predicated_vector_store(op);
4014 return;
4015 }
4016
4017 auto annotate_store = [&](StoreInst *store, const Expr &index) {
4018 add_tbaa_metadata(store, op->name, index);
4019 if (emit_atomic_stores) {
4020 store->setAtomic(AtomicOrdering::Monotonic);
4021 }
4022 };
4023
4024 Value *val = codegen(op->value);
4025 bool is_external = (external_buffer.find(op->name) != external_buffer.end());
4026
4027 if (value_type.is_scalar()) {
4028 // Scalar
4029 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type, op->index);
4030 StoreInst *store = builder->CreateAlignedStore(val, ptr, llvm::Align(value_type.bytes()));
4031 annotate_store(store, op->index);
4032 } else if (const Let *let = op->index.as<Let>()) {
4033 Stmt s = Store::make(op->name, op->value, let->body, op->param, op->predicate, op->alignment);
4034 codegen(LetStmt::make(let->name, let->value, s));
4035 } else {
4036 int alignment = value_type.bytes();
4037 const Ramp *ramp = op->index.as<Ramp>();
4038 if (ramp && is_const_one(ramp->stride)) {
4039
4040 int native_bits = native_vector_bits();
4041 int native_bytes = native_bits / 8;
4042
4043 // Boost the alignment if possible, up to the native vector width.
4044 ModulusRemainder mod_rem = op->alignment;
4045 while ((mod_rem.remainder & 1) == 0 &&
4046 (mod_rem.modulus & 1) == 0 &&
4047 alignment < native_bytes) {
4048 mod_rem.modulus /= 2;
4049 mod_rem.remainder /= 2;
4050 alignment *= 2;
4051 }
4052
4053 // If it is an external buffer, then we cannot assume that the host pointer
4054 // is aligned to at least the native vector width. However, we may be able to do
4055 // better than just assuming that it is unaligned.
4056 if (is_external && op->param.defined()) {
4057 int host_alignment = op->param.host_alignment();
4058 alignment = gcd(alignment, host_alignment);
4059 }
4060
4061 // For dense vector stores wider than the native vector
4062 // width, bust them up into native vectors.
4063 int store_lanes = value_type.lanes();
4064 int native_lanes = native_bits / value_type.bits();
4065
4066 for (int i = 0; i < store_lanes; i += native_lanes) {
4067 int slice_lanes = std::min(native_lanes, store_lanes - i);
4068 Expr slice_base = simplify(ramp->base + i);
4069 Expr slice_stride = make_one(slice_base.type());
4070 Expr slice_index = slice_lanes == 1 ? slice_base : Ramp::make(slice_base, slice_stride, slice_lanes);
4071 Value *slice_val = slice_vector(val, i, slice_lanes);
4072 Value *elt_ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type.element_of(), slice_base);
4073 Value *vec_ptr = builder->CreatePointerCast(elt_ptr, slice_val->getType()->getPointerTo());
4074 StoreInst *store = builder->CreateAlignedStore(slice_val, vec_ptr, llvm::Align(alignment));
4075 annotate_store(store, slice_index);
4076 }
4077 } else if (ramp) {
4078 Type ptr_type = value_type.element_of();
4079 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, ptr_type, ramp->base);
4080 const IntImm *const_stride = ramp->stride.as<IntImm>();
4081 Value *stride = codegen(ramp->stride);
4082 // Scatter without generating the indices as a vector
4083 for (int i = 0; i < ramp->lanes; i++) {
4084 Constant *lane = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i);
4085 Value *v = builder->CreateExtractElement(val, lane);
4086 if (const_stride) {
4087 // Use a constant offset from the base pointer
4088 Value *p =
4089 builder->CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_32(
4090 llvm_type_of(ptr_type),
4091 ptr,
4092 const_stride->value * i);
4093 StoreInst *store = builder->CreateStore(v, p);
4094 annotate_store(store, op->index);
4095 } else {
4096 // Increment the pointer by the stride for each element
4097 StoreInst *store = builder->CreateStore(v, ptr);
4098 annotate_store(store, op->index);
4099 ptr = builder->CreateInBoundsGEP(ptr, stride);
4100 }
4101 }
4102 } else {
4103 // Scatter
4104 Value *index = codegen(op->index);
4105 for (int i = 0; i < value_type.lanes(); i++) {
4106 Value *lane = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, i);
4107 Value *idx = builder->CreateExtractElement(index, lane);
4108 Value *v = builder->CreateExtractElement(val, lane);
4109 Value *ptr = codegen_buffer_pointer(op->name, value_type.element_of(), idx);
4110 StoreInst *store = builder->CreateStore(v, ptr);
4111 annotate_store(store, op->index);
4112 }
4113 }
4114 }
4115}

4117void CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_asserts(const vector<const AssertStmt *> &asserts) {
4118 if (target.has_feature(Target::NoAsserts)) {
4119 return;
4120 }
4121
4122 if (asserts.size() < 4) {
4123 for (const auto *a : asserts) {
4124 codegen(Stmt(a));
4125 }
4126 return;
4127 }
4128
4129 internal_assert(asserts.size() <= 63);
4130
4131 // Mix all the conditions together into a bitmask
4132
4133 Expr bitmask = cast<uint64_t>(1) << 63;
4134 for (size_t i = 0; i < asserts.size(); i++) {
4135 bitmask = bitmask | (cast<uint64_t>(!asserts[i]->condition) << i);
4136 }
4137
4138 Expr switch_case = count_trailing_zeros(bitmask);
4139
4140 BasicBlock *no_errors_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "no_errors_bb", function);
4141
4142 // Now switch on the bitmask to the correct failure
4143 Expr case_idx = cast<int32_t>(count_trailing_zeros(bitmask));
4144 llvm::SmallVector<uint32_t, 64> weights;
4145 weights.push_back(1 << 30);
4146 for (int i = 0; i < (int)asserts.size(); i++) {
4147 weights.push_back(0);
4148 }
4149 llvm::MDBuilder md_builder(*context);
4150 llvm::MDNode *switch_very_likely_branch = md_builder.createBranchWeights(weights);
4151 auto *switch_inst = builder->CreateSwitch(codegen(case_idx), no_errors_bb, asserts.size(), switch_very_likely_branch);
4152 for (int i = 0; i < (int)asserts.size(); i++) {
4153 BasicBlock *fail_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "assert_failed", function);
4154 switch_inst->addCase(ConstantInt::get(IntegerType::get(*context, 32), i), fail_bb);
4155 builder->SetInsertPoint(fail_bb);
4156 Value *v = codegen(asserts[i]->message);
4157 builder->CreateRet(v);
4158 }
4159 builder->SetInsertPoint(no_errors_bb);
4160}

4162void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Block *op) {
4163 // Peel blocks of assertions with pure conditions
4164 const AssertStmt *a = op->first.as<AssertStmt>();
4165 if (a && is_pure(a->condition)) {
4166 vector<const AssertStmt *> asserts;
4167 asserts.push_back(a);
4168 Stmt s = op->rest;
4169 while ((op = s.as<Block>()) && (a = op->first.as<AssertStmt>()) && is_pure(a->condition) && asserts.size() < 63) {
4170 asserts.push_back(a);
4171 s = op->rest;
4172 }
4173 codegen_asserts(asserts);
4174 codegen(s);
4175 } else {
4176 codegen(op->first);
4177 codegen(op->rest);
4178 }
4179}

4189void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const IfThenElse *op) {
4190
4191 // Gather the conditions and values in an if-else chain
4192 vector<pair<Expr, Stmt>> blocks;
4193 Stmt final_else;
4194 const IfThenElse *next_if = op;
4195 do {
4196 blocks.emplace_back(next_if->condition,
4197 next_if->then_case);
4198 final_else = next_if->else_case;
4199 next_if = final_else.defined() ? final_else.as<IfThenElse>() : nullptr;
4200 } while (next_if);
4201
4202 // Check if we should use a switch statement or an if-else tree
4203 Expr lhs;
4204 bool use_switch = blocks.size() > 1;
4205 vector<int> rhs;
4206 for (size_t i = 0; i < blocks.size(); i++) {
4207 const EQ *eq = blocks[i].first.as<EQ>();
4208 const int64_t *r = eq ? as_const_int(eq->b) : nullptr;
4209 if (eq &&
4210 r &&
4211 Int(32).can_represent(*r) &&
4212 is_pure(eq->a) &&
4213 is_const(eq->b) &&
4214 (!lhs.defined() || equal(lhs, eq->a))) {
4215 lhs = eq->a;
4216 rhs.push_back((int)*r);
4217 } else {
4218 use_switch = false;
4219 }
4220 }
4221
4222 if (use_switch) {
4223 // Conditions are all of the form expr == constant for a
4224 // consistent expr and different constants. Use a switch
4225 // statement.
4226
4227 BasicBlock *after_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "after_bb", function);
4228 BasicBlock *default_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "default_bb", function);
4229
4230 auto *switch_inst = builder->CreateSwitch(codegen(lhs), default_bb, blocks.size());
4231 for (int i = 0; i < (int)blocks.size(); i++) {
4232 string name = "case_" + std::to_string(rhs[i]) + "_bb";
4233 BasicBlock *case_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, name, function);
4234 switch_inst->addCase(ConstantInt::get(IntegerType::get(*context, 32), rhs[i]), case_bb);
4235 builder->SetInsertPoint(case_bb);
4236 codegen(blocks[i].second);
4237 builder->CreateBr(after_bb);
4238 }
4239
4240 builder->SetInsertPoint(default_bb);
4241 if (final_else.defined()) {
4242 codegen(final_else);
4243 }
4244 builder->CreateBr(after_bb);
4245
4246 builder->SetInsertPoint(after_bb);
4247 } else {
4248 // Codegen an regular if-else chain using branches.
4249
4250 BasicBlock *after_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "after_bb", function);
4251
4252 for (const auto &p : blocks) {
4253 BasicBlock *then_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "then_bb", function);
4254 BasicBlock *next_bb = BasicBlock::Create(*context, "next_bb", function);
4255 builder->CreateCondBr(codegen(p.first), then_bb, next_bb);
4256 builder->SetInsertPoint(then_bb);
4257 codegen(p.second);
4258 builder->CreateBr(after_bb);
4259 builder->SetInsertPoint(next_bb);
4260 }
4261
4262 if (final_else.defined()) {
4263 codegen(final_else);
4264 }
4265 builder->CreateBr(after_bb);
4266
4267 builder->SetInsertPoint(after_bb);
4268 }
4269}

4274 // Discard result

4278void CodeGen_LLVM::visit(const Shuffle *op) {
4279 vector<Value *> vecs;
4280 for (const Expr &e : op->vectors) {
4281 vecs.push_back(codegen(e));
4282 }
4283
4284 if (op->is_interleave()) {
4285 value = interleave_vectors(vecs);
4286 } else {
4287 // If the even-numbered indices equal the odd-numbered
4288 // indices, only generate one and then do a self-interleave.
4289 for (int f : {4, 3, 2}) {
4290 bool self_interleave = (op->indices.size() % f) == 0;
4291 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->indices.size(); i++) {
4292 self_interleave &= (op->indices[i] == op->indices[i - (i % f)]);
4293 }
4294 if (self_interleave) {
4295 vector<int> sub_indices;
4296 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->indices.size(); i += f) {
4297 sub_indices.push_back(op->indices[i]);
4298 }
4299 Expr equiv = Shuffle::make(op->vectors, sub_indices);
4300 value = codegen(equiv);
4301 value = interleave_vectors(std::vector<Value *>(f, value));
4302 return;
4303 }
4304
4305 // Check for an interleave of slices (i.e. an in-vector transpose)
4306 bool interleave_of_slices = op->vectors.size() == 1 && (op->indices.size() % f) == 0;
4307 int step = op->type.lanes() / f;
4308 for (int i = 0; i < step; i++) {
4309 for (int j = 0; j < f; j++) {
4310 interleave_of_slices &= (op->indices[i * f + j] == j * step + i);
4311 }
4312 }
4313 if (interleave_of_slices) {
4314 value = codegen(op->vectors[0]);
4315 vector<Value *> slices;
4316 for (int i = 0; i < f; i++) {
4317 slices.push_back(slice_vector(value, i * step, step));
4318 }
4319 value = interleave_vectors(slices);
4320 }
4321 }
4322 // If the indices form contiguous aligned runs, do the shuffle
4323 // on entire sub-vectors by reinterpreting them as a wider
4324 // type.
4325 for (int f : {8, 4, 2}) {
4326 if (op->type.lanes() % f != 0) {
4327 continue;
4328 }
4329
4330 if (op->type.bits() * f > 64) {
4331 continue;
4332 }
4333 bool contiguous = true;
4334 for (const Expr &vec : op->vectors) {
4335 contiguous &= ((vec.type().lanes() % f) == 0);
4336 }
4337 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->indices.size(); i += f) {
4338 contiguous &= (op->indices[i] % f) == 0;
4339 for (int j = 0; j < f; j++) {
4340 contiguous &= (op->indices[i + j] == op->indices[i] + j);
4341 }
4342 }
4343 if (contiguous) {
4344 vector<Expr> equiv_args;
4345 for (const Expr &vec : op->vectors) {
4346 Type t = UInt(vec.type().bits() * f, vec.type().lanes() / f);
4347 equiv_args.push_back(reinterpret(t, vec));
4348 }
4349 vector<int> equiv_indices;
4350 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->indices.size(); i += f) {
4351 equiv_indices.push_back(op->indices[i] / f);
4352 }
4353 Expr equiv = Shuffle::make(equiv_args, equiv_indices);
4354 equiv = reinterpret(op->type, equiv);
4355 codegen(equiv);
4356 return;
4357 }
4358 }
4359
4360 // Do a concat and then a single shuffle
4361 value = concat_vectors(vecs);
4362 if (op->is_concat()) {
4363 // If this is just a concat, we're done.
4364 } else if (op->is_slice() && op->slice_stride() == 1) {
4365 value = slice_vector(value, op->indices[0], op->indices.size());
4366 } else {
4367 value = shuffle_vectors(value, op->indices);
4368 }
4369 }
4370
4371 if (op->type.is_scalar() && value->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
4372 value = builder->CreateExtractElement(value, ConstantInt::get(i32_t, 0));
4373 }
4374}
