4378}
4379
4380void CodeGen_LLVM::codegen_vector_reduce(const VectorReduce *op, const Expr &init) {
4381 Expr val = op->value;
4382 const int output_lanes = op->type.lanes();
4383 const int native_lanes = native_vector_bits() / op->type.bits();
4384 const int factor = val.type().lanes() / output_lanes;
4385
4386 Expr (*binop)(Expr, Expr) = nullptr;
4387 switch (op->op) {
4388 case VectorReduce::Add:
4389 binop = Add::make;
4390 break;
4391 case VectorReduce::Mul:
4392 binop = Mul::make;
4393 break;
4394 case VectorReduce::Min:
4395 binop = Min::make;
4396 break;
4397 case VectorReduce::Max:
4398 binop = Max::make;
4399 break;
4400 case VectorReduce::And:
4401 binop = And::make;
4402 break;
4403 case VectorReduce::Or:
4404 binop = Or::make;
4405 break;
4406 case VectorReduce::SaturatingAdd:
4407 binop = saturating_add;
4408 break;
4409 }
4410
4411 if (op->type.is_bool() && op->op == VectorReduce::Or) {
4412 // Cast to u8, use max, cast back to bool.
4413 Expr equiv = cast(op->value.type().with_bits(8), op->value);
4414 equiv = VectorReduce::make(VectorReduce::Max, equiv, op->type.lanes());
4415 if (init.defined()) {
4416 equiv = max(equiv, init);
4417 }
4418 equiv = cast(op->type, equiv);
4419 equiv.accept(this);
4420 return;
4421 }
4422
4423 if (op->type.is_bool() && op->op == VectorReduce::And) {
4424 // Cast to u8, use min, cast back to bool.
4425 Expr equiv = cast(op->value.type().with_bits(8), op->value);
4426 equiv = VectorReduce::make(VectorReduce::Min, equiv, op->type.lanes());
4427 equiv = cast(op->type, equiv);
4428 if (init.defined()) {
4429 equiv = min(equiv, init);
4430 }
4431 equiv.accept(this);
4432 return;
4433 }
4434
4435 if (op->type.element_of() == Float(16)) {
4436 Expr equiv = cast(op->value.type().with_bits(32), op->value);
4437 equiv = VectorReduce::make(op->op, equiv, op->type.lanes());
4438 if (init.defined()) {
4439 equiv = binop(equiv, init);
4440 }
4441 equiv = cast(op->type, equiv);
4442 equiv.accept(this);
4443 return;
4444 }
4445
4446 if (output_lanes == 1) {
4447 const int input_lanes = val.type().lanes();
4448 const int input_bytes = input_lanes * val.type().bytes();
4449 const bool llvm_has_intrinsic =
4450 // Must be one of these ops
4451 ((op->op == VectorReduce::Add ||
4452 op->op == VectorReduce::Mul ||
4453 op->op == VectorReduce::Min ||
4454 op->op == VectorReduce::Max) &&
4455 // Must be a power of two lanes
4456 (input_lanes >= 2) &&
4457 ((input_lanes & (input_lanes - 1)) == 0) &&
4458 // int versions exist up to 1024 bits
4459 ((!op->type.is_float() && input_bytes <= 1024) ||
4460 // float versions exist up to 16 lanes
4461 input_lanes <= 16) &&
4462 // As of the release of llvm 10, the 64-bit experimental total
4463 // reductions don't seem to be done yet on arm.
4464 (val.type().bits() != 64 ||
4465 target.arch != Target::ARM));
4466
4467 if (llvm_has_intrinsic) {
4468 std::stringstream name;
4469#if LLVM_VERSION >= 120
4470 name << "llvm.vector.reduce.";
4471#else
4472 name << "llvm.experimental.vector.reduce.";
4473#endif
4474 const int bits = op->type.bits();
4475 bool takes_initial_value = false;
4476 Expr initial_value = init;
4477 if (op->type.is_float()) {
4478 switch (op->op) {
4479 case VectorReduce::Add:
4480#if LLVM_VERSION >= 120
4481 name << "fadd";
4482#else
4483 name << "v2.fadd.f" << bits;
4484#endif
4485 takes_initial_value = true;
4486 if (!initial_value.defined()) {
4487 initial_value = make_zero(op->type);
4488 }
4489 break;
4490 case VectorReduce::Mul:
4491#if LLVM_VERSION >= 120
4492 name << "fmul";
4493#else
4494 name << "v2.fmul.f" << bits;
4495#endif
4496 takes_initial_value = true;
4497 if (!initial_value.defined()) {
4498 initial_value = make_one(op->type);
4499 }
4500 break;
4501 case VectorReduce::Min:
4502 name << "fmin";
4503 break;
4504 case VectorReduce::Max:
4505 name << "fmax";
4506 break;
4507 default:
4508 break;
4509 }
4510 } else if (op->type.is_int() || op->type.is_uint()) {
4511 switch (op->op) {
4512 case VectorReduce::Add:
4513 name << "add";
4514 break;
4515 case VectorReduce::Mul:
4516 name << "mul";
4517 break;
4518 case VectorReduce::Min:
4519 name << (op->type.is_int() ? 's' : 'u') << "min";
4520 break;
4521 case VectorReduce::Max:
4522 name << (op->type.is_int() ? 's' : 'u') << "max";
4523 break;
4524 default:
4525 break;
4526 }
4527 }
4528 name << ".v" << val.type().lanes() << (op->type.is_float() ? 'f' : 'i') << bits;
4529
4530 string intrin_name = name.str();
4531
4532 vector<Expr> args;
4533 if (takes_initial_value) {
4534 args.push_back(initial_value);
4535 initial_value = Expr();
4536 }
4537 args.push_back(op->value);
4538
4539 // Make sure the declaration exists, or the codegen for
4540 // call will assume that the args should scalarize.
4541 if (!module->getFunction(intrin_name)) {
4542 vector<llvm::Type *> arg_types;
4543 for (const Expr &e : args) {
4544 arg_types.push_back(llvm_type_of(e.type()));
4545 }
4546 FunctionType *func_t = FunctionType::get(llvm_type_of(op->type), arg_types, false);
4547 llvm::Function::Create(func_t, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, intrin_name, module.get());
4548 }
4549
4550 Expr equiv = Call::make(op->type, intrin_name, args, Call::PureExtern);
4551 if (initial_value.defined()) {
4552 equiv = binop(initial_value, equiv);
4553 }
4554 equiv.accept(this);
4555 return;
4556 }
4557 }
4558
4559 if (output_lanes == 1 &&
4560 factor > native_lanes &&
4561 factor % native_lanes == 0) {
4562 // It's a total reduction of multiple native
4563 // vectors. Start by adding the vectors together.
4564 Expr equiv;
4565 for (int i = 0; i < factor / native_lanes; i++) {
4566 Expr next = Shuffle::make_slice(val, i * native_lanes, 1, native_lanes);
4567 if (equiv.defined()) {
4568 equiv = binop(equiv, next);
4569 } else {
4570 equiv = next;
4571 }
4572 }
4573 equiv = VectorReduce::make(op->op, equiv, 1);
4574 if (init.defined()) {
4575 equiv = binop(equiv, init);
4576 }
4577 equiv = common_subexpression_elimination(equiv);
4578 equiv.accept(this);
4579 return;
4580 }
4581
4582 if (factor > 2 && ((factor & 1) == 0)) {
4583 // Factor the reduce into multiple stages. If we're going to
4584 // be widening the type by 4x or more we should also factor the
4585 // widening into multiple stages.
4586 Type intermediate_type = op->value.type().with_lanes(op->value.type().lanes() / 2);
4587 Expr equiv = VectorReduce::make(op->op, op->value, intermediate_type.lanes());
4588 if (op->op == VectorReduce::Add &&
4589 (op->type.is_int() || op->type.is_uint()) &&
4590 op->type.bits() >= 32) {
4591 Type narrower_type = op->value.type().narrow().narrow();
4592 Expr narrower = lossless_cast(narrower_type, op->value);
4593 if (!narrower.defined() && narrower_type.is_int()) {
4594 // Maybe we can narrow to an unsigned int instead.
4595 narrower_type = narrower_type.with_code(Type::UInt);
4596 narrower = lossless_cast(narrower_type, op->value);
4597 }
4598 if (narrower.defined()) {
4599 // Widen it by 2x before the horizontal add
4600 narrower = cast(narrower.type().widen(), narrower);
4601 equiv = VectorReduce::make(op->op, narrower, intermediate_type.lanes());
4602 // Then widen it by 2x again afterwards
4603 equiv = cast(intermediate_type, equiv);
4604 }
4605 }
4606 equiv = VectorReduce::make(op->op, equiv, op->type.lanes());
4607 if (init.defined()) {
4608 equiv = binop(equiv, init);
4609 }
4610 equiv = common_subexpression_elimination(equiv);
4611 codegen(equiv);
4612 return;
4613 }
4614
4615 // Extract each slice and combine
4616 Expr equiv = init;
4617 for (int i = 0; i < factor; i++) {
4618 Expr next = Shuffle::make_slice(val, i, factor, val.type().lanes() / factor);
4619 if (equiv.defined()) {
4620 equiv = binop(equiv, next);
4621 } else {
4622 equiv = next;
4623 }
4624 }
4625 equiv = common_subexpression_elimination(equiv);
4626 codegen(equiv);
4627} // namespace Internal

4643Value *CodeGen_LLVM::create_alloca_at_entry(llvm::Type *t, int n, bool zero_initialize, const string &name) {
4644 IRBuilderBase::InsertPoint here = builder->saveIP();
4645 BasicBlock *entry = &builder->GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getEntryBlock();
4646 if (entry->empty()) {
4647 builder->SetInsertPoint(entry);
4648 } else {
4649 builder->SetInsertPoint(entry, entry->getFirstInsertionPt());
4650 }
4651 Value *size = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, n);
4652 AllocaInst *ptr = builder->CreateAlloca(t, size, name);
4653 int align = native_vector_bits() / 8;
4654 llvm::DataLayout d(module.get());
4655 int allocated_size = n * (int)d.getTypeAllocSize(t);
4656 if (t->isVectorTy() || n > 1) {
4657 ptr->setAlignment(llvm::Align(align));
4658 }
4659 requested_alloca_total += allocated_size;
4660
4661 if (zero_initialize) {
4662 if (n == 1) {
4663 builder->CreateStore(Constant::getNullValue(t), ptr);
4664 } else {
4665 builder->CreateMemSet(ptr, Constant::getNullValue(t), n, llvm::Align(align));
4666 }
4667 }
4668 builder->restoreIP(here);
4669 return ptr;
4670}

4722
4723Value *CodeGen_LLVM::call_overloaded_intrin(const Type &result_type, const std::string &name, const std::vector<Expr> &args) {
4724 constexpr int debug_level = 4;
4725
4726 debug(debug_level) << "call_overloaded_intrin: " << result_type << " " << name << "(";
4727 const char *comma = "";
4728 for (const Expr &i : args) {
4729 debug(debug_level) << comma << i;
4730 comma = ", ";
4731 }
4732 debug(debug_level) << ")\n";
4733
4734 auto impls_i = intrinsics.find(name);
4735 if (impls_i == intrinsics.end()) {
4736 debug(debug_level) << "No intrinsic " << name << "\n";
4737 return nullptr;
4738 }
4739
4740 const Intrinsic *resolved = nullptr;
4741 for (const Intrinsic &overload : impls_i->second) {
4742 debug(debug_level) << "Considering candidate " << overload.result_type << "(";
4743 const char *comma = "";
4744 for (const auto &i : overload.arg_types) {
4745 debug(debug_level) << comma << i;
4746 comma = ", ";
4747 }
4748 debug(debug_level) << ")\n";
4749 if (overload.arg_types.size() != args.size()) {
4750 debug(debug_level) << "Wrong number of arguments\n";
4751 continue;
4752 }
4753
4754 if (overload.result_type.element_of() != result_type.element_of()) {
4755 debug(debug_level) << "Wrong result type\n";
4756 continue;
4757 }
4758
4759 bool match = true;
4760 for (int i = 0; i < (int)overload.arg_types.size(); i++) {
4761 if (args[i].type().is_scalar()) {
4762 // Allow lossless casting for scalar arguments, and
4763 // allow broadcasting to vector arguments.
4764 if (!lossless_cast(overload.arg_types[i].element_of(), args[i]).defined()) {
4765 match = false;
4766 debug(debug_level) << "Cannot promote scalar argument " << i << "\n";
4767 break;
4768 }
4769 } else {
4770 int required_lanes = result_type.lanes() * overload.arg_types[i].lanes() / overload.result_type.lanes();
4771 if (required_lanes != args[i].type().lanes()) {
4772 match = false;
4773 debug(debug_level) << "Need " << required_lanes << " lanes for argument " << i << "\n";
4774 break;
4775 }
4776
4777 // Vector arguments must be exact.
4778 if (overload.arg_types[i].element_of() != args[i].type().element_of()) {
4779 match = false;
4780 debug(debug_level) << "Vector types not equal " << i << "\n";
4781 break;
4782 }
4783 }
4784 }
4785 if (!match) {
4786 continue;
4787 }
4788
4789 if (!resolved) {
4790 debug(debug_level) << "Resolved!\n";
4791 resolved = &overload;
4792 } else {
4793 if (resolved->result_type.lanes() < result_type.lanes()) {
4794 // The current match is smaller than the result type. Take the bigger intrinsic.
4795 if (overload.result_type.lanes() > resolved->result_type.lanes()) {
4796 debug(debug_level) << "Replaced with bigger intrinsic\n";
4797 resolved = &overload;
4798 }
4799 } else {
4800 // The current match is bigger than the result type. If the current candidate is also bigger,
4801 // but smaller than the current match, take it instead.
4802 if (overload.result_type.lanes() >= result_type.lanes() && overload.result_type.lanes() < resolved->result_type.lanes()) {
4803 debug(debug_level) << "Replaced with smaller intrinsic\n";
4804 resolved = &overload;
4805 }
4806 }
4807 }
4808 }
4809
4810 if (resolved) {
4811 std::vector<Expr> promoted_args;
4812 promoted_args.reserve(args.size());
4813 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.size(); i++) {
4814 Expr promoted_arg = args[i];
4815 if (args[i].type().is_scalar()) {
4816 promoted_arg = lossless_cast(resolved->arg_types[i].element_of(), promoted_arg);
4817 }
4818 if (resolved->arg_types[i].is_vector() && args[i].type().is_scalar() && result_type.lanes() > 1) {
4819 // We're passing a scalar to a vector argument, broadcast it.
4820 promoted_args.emplace_back(Broadcast::make(promoted_arg, result_type.lanes()));
4821 } else {
4822 promoted_args.emplace_back(promoted_arg);
4823 }
4824 internal_assert(promoted_args.back().defined());
4825 }
4826 return call_intrin(result_type, resolved->result_type.lanes(), resolved->impl, promoted_args);
4827 } else {
4828 debug(debug_level) << "Unresolved intrinsic " << name << "\n";
4829 }
4830 return nullptr;
4831}

4881
4882Value *CodeGen_LLVM::call_intrin(llvm::Type *result_type, int intrin_lanes,
4883 llvm::Function *intrin, vector<Value *> arg_values) {
4884 internal_assert(intrin);
4885 int arg_lanes = 1;
4886 if (result_type->isVectorTy()) {
4887 arg_lanes = get_vector_num_elements(result_type);
4888 }
4889
4890 if (intrin_lanes != arg_lanes) {
4891 // Cut up each arg into appropriately-sized pieces, call the
4892 // intrinsic on each, then splice together the results.
4893 vector<Value *> results;
4894 for (int start = 0; start < arg_lanes; start += intrin_lanes) {
4895 vector<Value *> args;
4896 for (size_t i = 0; i < arg_values.size(); i++) {
4897 int arg_i_lanes = 1;
4898 if (arg_values[i]->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
4899 arg_i_lanes = get_vector_num_elements(arg_values[i]->getType());
4900 }
4901
4902 if (arg_i_lanes >= arg_lanes) {
4903 // Horizontally reducing intrinsics may have
4904 // arguments that have more lanes than the
4905 // result. Assume that the horizontally reduce
4906 // neighboring elements...
4907 int reduce = arg_i_lanes / arg_lanes;
4908 args.push_back(slice_vector(arg_values[i], start * reduce, intrin_lanes * reduce));
4909 } else if (arg_i_lanes == 1) {
4910 if (intrin->getFunctionType()->getParamType(i)->isVectorTy()) {
4911 // It's a scalar argument to a vector parameter. Broadcast it.
4912 // Overwriting the parameter means this only happens once.
4913 arg_values[i] = create_broadcast(arg_values[i], intrin_lanes);
4914 } else {
4915 // It's a scalar arg to an intrinsic that returns
4916 // a vector. Replicate it over the slices.
4917 }
4918 args.push_back(arg_values[i]);
4919 } else {
4920 internal_error << "Argument in call_intrin has " << arg_i_lanes
4921 << " with result type having " << arg_lanes << "\n";
4922 }
4923 }
4924
4925 llvm::Type *result_slice_type =
4926 get_vector_type(result_type->getScalarType(), intrin_lanes);
4927
4928 results.push_back(call_intrin(result_slice_type, intrin_lanes, intrin, args));
4929 }
4930 Value *result = concat_vectors(results);
4931 return slice_vector(result, 0, arg_lanes);
4932 }
4933
4934 llvm::FunctionType *intrin_type = intrin->getFunctionType();
4935 for (int i = 0; i < (int)arg_values.size(); i++) {
4936 if (arg_values[i]->getType() != intrin_type->getParamType(i)) {
4937 // There can be some mismatches in types, such as when passing scalar Halide type T
4938 // to LLVM vector type <1 x T>.
4939 arg_values[i] = builder->CreateBitCast(arg_values[i], intrin_type->getParamType(i));
4940 }
4941 }
4942
4943 CallInst *call = builder->CreateCall(intrin, arg_values);
4944 return call;
4945}
4946
4947Value *CodeGen_LLVM::slice_vector(Value *vec, int start, int size) {
4948 // Force the arg to be an actual vector
4949 if (!vec->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
4950 vec = create_broadcast(vec, 1);
4951 }
4952
4953 int vec_lanes = get_vector_num_elements(vec->getType());
4954
4955 if (start == 0 && size == vec_lanes) {
4956 return vec;
4957 }
4958
4959 if (size == 1) {
4960 return builder->CreateExtractElement(vec, (uint64_t)start);
4961 }
4962
4963 vector<int> indices(size);
4964 for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4965 int idx = start + i;
4966 if (idx >= 0 && idx < vec_lanes) {
4967 indices[i] = idx;
4968 } else {
4969 indices[i] = -1;
4970 }
4971 }
4972 return shuffle_vectors(vec, indices);
4973}
4974
4975Value *CodeGen_LLVM::concat_vectors(const vector<Value *> &v) {
4976 if (v.size() == 1) {
4977 return v[0];
4978 }
4979
4980 internal_assert(!v.empty());
4981
4982 vector<Value *> vecs = v;
4983
4984 // Force them all to be actual vectors
4985 for (Value *&val : vecs) {
4986 if (!val->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
4987 val = create_broadcast(val, 1);
4988 }
4989 }
4990
4991 while (vecs.size() > 1) {
4992 vector<Value *> new_vecs;
4993
4994 for (size_t i = 0; i < vecs.size() - 1; i += 2) {
4995 Value *v1 = vecs[i];
4996 Value *v2 = vecs[i + 1];
4997
4998 int w1 = get_vector_num_elements(v1->getType());
4999 int w2 = get_vector_num_elements(v2->getType());
5000
5001 // Possibly pad one of the vectors to match widths.
5002 if (w1 < w2) {
5003 v1 = slice_vector(v1, 0, w2);
5004 } else if (w2 < w1) {
5005 v2 = slice_vector(v2, 0, w1);
5006 }
5007 int w_matched = std::max(w1, w2);
5008
5009 internal_assert(v1->getType() == v2->getType());
5010
5011 vector<int> indices(w1 + w2);
5012 for (int i = 0; i < w1; i++) {
5013 indices[i] = i;
5014 }
5015 for (int i = 0; i < w2; i++) {
5016 indices[w1 + i] = w_matched + i;
5017 }
5018
5019 Value *merged = shuffle_vectors(v1, v2, indices);
5020
5021 new_vecs.push_back(merged);
5022 }
5023
5024 // If there were an odd number of them, we need to also push
5025 // the one that didn't get merged.
5026 if (vecs.size() & 1) {
5027 new_vecs.push_back(vecs.back());
5028 }
5029
5030 vecs.swap(new_vecs);
5031 }
5032
5033 return vecs[0];
5034}
5035
5036Value *CodeGen_LLVM::shuffle_vectors(Value *a, Value *b,
5037 const std::vector<int> &indices) {
5038 internal_assert(a->getType() == b->getType());
5039 if (!a->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
5040 a = create_broadcast(a, 1);
5041 b = create_broadcast(b, 1);
5042 }
5043 vector<Constant *> llvm_indices(indices.size());
5044 for (size_t i = 0; i < llvm_indices.size(); i++) {
5045 if (indices[i] >= 0) {
5046 internal_assert(indices[i] < get_vector_num_elements(a->getType()) * 2);
5047 llvm_indices[i] = ConstantInt::get(i32_t, indices[i]);
5048 } else {
5049 // Only let -1 be undef.
5050 internal_assert(indices[i] == -1);
5051 llvm_indices[i] = UndefValue::get(i32_t);
5052 }
5053 }
5054 return builder->CreateShuffleVector(a, b, ConstantVector::get(llvm_indices));
5055}
5056
5057Value *CodeGen_LLVM::shuffle_vectors(Value *a, const std::vector<int> &indices) {
5058 Value *b = UndefValue::get(a->getType());
5059 return shuffle_vectors(a, b, indices);
5060}

5062std::pair<llvm::Function *, int> CodeGen_LLVM::find_vector_runtime_function(const std::string &name, int lanes) {
5063 // Check if a vector version of the function already
5064 // exists at some useful width. We use the naming
5065 // convention that a N-wide version of a function foo is
5066 // called fooxN. All of our intrinsics are power-of-two
5067 // sized, so starting at the first power of two >= the
5068 // vector width, we'll try all powers of two in decreasing
5069 // order.
5070 vector<int> sizes_to_try;
5071 int l = 1;
5072 while (l < lanes) {
5073 l *= 2;
5074 }
5075 for (int i = l; i > 1; i /= 2) {
5076 sizes_to_try.push_back(i);
5077 }
5078
5079 // If none of those match, we'll also try doubling
5080 // the lanes up to the next power of two (this is to catch
5081 // cases where we're a 64-bit vector and have a 128-bit
5082 // vector implementation).
5083 sizes_to_try.push_back(l * 2);
5084
5085 for (size_t i = 0; i < sizes_to_try.size(); i++) {
5086 int l = sizes_to_try[i];
5087 llvm::Function *vec_fn = module->getFunction(name + "x" + std::to_string(l));
5088 if (vec_fn) {
5089 return {vec_fn, l};
5090 }
5091 }
5092
5093 return {nullptr, 0};
5094}
